40原 9:27 As Jesus went on from there, two blind men followed him, crying loudly, "Have mercy on us, Son of David!"
40原 9:28 When he entered the house, the blind men came to him; and Jesus said to them, "Do you believe that I am able to do this?" They said to him, "Yes, Lord."
40原 9:29 Then he touched their eyes and said, "According to your faith let it be done to you."
40原 9:30 And their eyes were opened. Then Jesus sternly ordered them, "See that no one knows of this."
40原 9:31 But they went away and spread the news about him throughout that district.
40原 9:32 After they had gone away, a demoniac who was mute was brought to him.
40原 9:33 And when the demon had been cast out, the one who had been mute spoke; and the crowds were amazed and said, "Never has anything like this been seen in Israel."
40原 9:34 But the Pharisees said, "By the ruler of the demons he casts out the demons."
40原 9:35 Then Jesus went about all the cities and villages, teaching in their synagogues, and proclaiming the good news of the kingdom, and curing every disease and every sickness.
40原 9:36 When he saw the crowds, he had compassion for them, because they were harassed and helpless, like sheep without a shepherd.
40原 9:37 Then he said to his disciples, "The harvest is plentiful, but the laborers are few;
