40原 10:1 Then Jesus summoned his twelve disciples and gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to cure every disease and every sickness.
40原 10:2 These are the names of the twelve apostles: first, Simon, also known as Peter, and his brother Andrew; James son of Zebedee, and his brother John;
40原 10:3 Philip and Bartholomew; Thomas and Matthew the tax collector; James son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus;
40原 10:4 Simon the Cananaean, and Judas Iscariot, the one who betrayed him.
40原 10:5 These twelve Jesus sent out with the following instructions: "Go nowhere among the Gentiles, and enter no town of the Samaritans,
40原 10:6 but go rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
40原 10:7 As you go, proclaim the good news, 'The kingdom of heaven has come near.'
40原 10:8 Cure the sick, raise the dead, cleanse the lepers, cast out demons. You received without payment; give without payment.
40原 10:9 Take no gold, or silver, or copper in your belts,
40原 10:10 no bag for your journey, or two tunics, or sandals, or a staff; for laborers deserve their food.
40原 10:11 Whatever town or village you enter, find out who in it is worthy, and stay there until you leave.
40原 10:12 As you enter the house, greet it.
40原 10:13 If the house is worthy, let your peace come upon it; but if it is not worthy, let your peace return to you.
40原 10:14 If anyone will not welcome you or listen to your words, shake off the dust from your feet as you leave that house or town.
40原 10:15 Truly I tell you, it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrah on the day of judgment than for that town.
40原 10:16 "See, I am sending you out like sheep into the midst of wolves; so be wise as serpents and innocent as doves.
40原 10:17 Beware of them, for they will hand you over to councils and flog you in their synagogues;
40原 10:18 and you will be dragged before governors and kings because of me, as a testimony to them and the Gentiles.
40原 10:19 When they hand you over, do not worry about how you are to speak or what you are to say; for what you are to say will be given to you at that time;
40原 10:20 for it is not you who speak, but the Spirit of your Father speaking through you.
40原 10:21 Brother will betray brother to death, and a father his child, and children will rise against parents and have them put to death;
40原 10:22 and you will be hated by all because of my name. But the one who endures to the end will be saved.
40原 10:23 When they persecute you in one town, flee to the next; for truly I tell you, you will not have gone through all the towns of Israel before the Son of Man comes.
40原 10:24 "A disciple is not above the teacher, nor a slave above the master;
40原 10:25 it is enough for the disciple to be like the teacher, and the slave like the master. If they have called the master of the house Beelzebul, how much more will they malign those of his household!
40原 10:26 "So have no fear of them; for nothing is covered up that will not be uncovered, and nothing secret that will not become known.
40原 10:27 What I say to you in the dark, tell in the light; and what you hear whispered, proclaim from the housetops.
40原 10:28 Do not fear those who kill the body but cannot kill the soul; rather fear him who can destroy both soul and body in hell.
40原 10:29 Are not two sparrows sold for a penny? Yet not one of them will fall to the ground apart from your Father.
40原 10:30 And even the hairs of your head are all counted.
40原 10:31 So do not be afraid; you are of more value than many sparrows.
40原 10:32 "Everyone therefore who acknowledges me before others, I also will acknowledge before my Father in heaven;
40原 10:33 but whoever denies me before others, I also will deny before my Father in heaven.
40原 10:34 "Do not think that I have come to bring peace to the earth; I have not come to bring peace, but a sword.
40原 10:35 For I have come to set a man against his father, and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law;
40原 10:36 and one's foes will be members of one's own household.
40原 10:37 Whoever loves father or mother more than me is not worthy of me; and whoever loves son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me;
40原 10:38 and whoever does not take up the cross and follow me is not worthy of me.
40原 10:39 Those who find their life will lose it, and those who lose their life for my sake will find it.
40原 10:40 "Whoever welcomes you welcomes me, and whoever welcomes me welcomes the one who sent me.
40原 10:41 Whoever welcomes a prophet in the name of a prophet will receive a prophet's reward; and whoever welcomes a righteous person in the name of a righteous person will receive the reward of the righteous;
40原 10:42 and whoever gives even a cup of cold water to one of these little ones in the name of a disciple--truly I tell you, none of these will lose their reward."
40原 11:1 Now when Jesus had finished instructing his twelve disciples, he went on from there to teach and proclaim his message in their cities.
40原 11:2 When John heard in prison what the Messiah was doing, he sent word by his disciples
40原 11:3 and said to him, "Are you the one who is to come, or are we to wait for another?"
40原 11:4 Jesus answered them, "Go and tell John what you hear and see:
40原 11:5 the blind receive their sight, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, and the poor have good news brought to them.
40原 11:6 And blessed is anyone who takes no offense at me."
40原 11:7 As they went away, Jesus began to speak to the crowds about John: "What did you go out into the wilderness to look at? A reed shaken by the wind?
40原 11:8 What then did you go out to see? Someone dressed in soft robes? Look, those who wear soft robes are in royal palaces.
40原 11:9 What then did you go out to see? A prophet? Yes, I tell you, and more than a prophet.
40原 11:10 This is the one about whom it is written, 'See, I am sending my messenger ahead of you, who will prepare your way before you.'
40原 11:11 Truly I tell you, among those born of women no one has arisen greater than John the Baptist; yet the least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.
40原 11:12 From the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven has suffered violence, and the violent take it by force.
40原 11:13 For all the prophets and the law prophesied until John came;
40原 11:14 and if you are willing to accept it, he is Elijah who is to come.
40原 11:15 Let anyone with ears listen!
40原 11:16 "But to what will I compare this generation? It is like children sitting in the marketplaces and calling to one another,
40原 11:17 'We played the flute for you, and you did not dance; we wailed, and you did not mourn.'
40原 11:18 For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, 'He has a demon';
40原 11:19 the Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they say, 'Look, a glutton and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners!' Yet wisdom is vindicated by her deeds."
40原 11:20 Then he began to reproach the cities in which most of his deeds of power had been done, because they did not repent.
40原 11:21 "Woe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the deeds of power done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.
40原 11:22 But I tell you, on the day of judgment it will be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon than for you.
40原 11:23 And you, Capernaum, will you be exalted to heaven? No, you will be brought down to Hades. For if the deeds of power done in you had been done in Sodom, it would have remained until this day.
40原 11:24 But I tell you that on the day of judgment it will be more tolerable for the land of Sodom than for you."
40原 11:25 At that time Jesus said, "I thank you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because you have hidden these things from the wise and the intelligent and have revealed them to infants;
40原 11:26 yes, Father, for such was your gracious will.
40原 11:27 All things have been handed over to me by my Father; and no one knows the Son except the Father, and no one knows the Father except the Son and anyone to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.
40原 11:28 "Come to me, all you that are weary and are carrying heavy burdens, and I will give you rest.
40原 11:29 Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me; for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.
40原 11:30 For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light."
40原 12:1 At that time Jesus went through the grainfields on the sabbath; his disciples were hungry, and they began to pluck heads of grain and to eat.
40原 12:2 When the Pharisees saw it, they said to him, "Look, your disciples are doing what is not lawful to do on the sabbath."
40原 12:3 He said to them, "Have you not read what David did when he and his companions were hungry?
40原 12:4 He entered the house of God and ate the bread of the Presence, which it was not lawful for him or his companions to eat, but only for the priests.
40原 12:5 Or have you not read in the law that on the sabbath the priests in the temple break the sabbath and yet are guiltless?
40原 12:6 I tell you, something greater than the temple is here.
40原 12:7 But if you had known what this means, 'I desire mercy and not sacrifice,' you would not have condemned the guiltless.
40原 12:8 For the Son of Man is lord of the sabbath."
40原 12:9 He left that place and entered their synagogue;
40原 12:10 a man was there with a withered hand, and they asked him, "Is it lawful to cure on the sabbath?" so that they might accuse him.
40原 12:11 He said to them, "Suppose one of you has only one sheep and it falls into a pit on the sabbath; will you not lay hold of it and lift it out?
40原 12:12 How much more valuable is a human being than a sheep! So it is lawful to do good on the sabbath."
40原 12:13 Then he said to the man, "Stretch out your hand." He stretched it out, and it was restored, as sound as the other.
40原 12:14 But the Pharisees went out and conspired against him, how to destroy him.
40原 12:15 When Jesus became aware of this, he departed. Many crowds followed him, and he cured all of them,
40原 12:16 and he ordered them not to make him known.
40原 12:17 This was to fulfill what had been spoken through the prophet Isaiah:
40原 12:18 "Here is my servant, whom I have chosen, my beloved, with whom my soul is well pleased. I will put my Spirit upon him, and he will proclaim justice to the Gentiles.
40原 12:19 He will not wrangle or cry aloud, nor will anyone hear his voice in the streets.
40原 12:20 He will not break a bruised reed or quench a smoldering wick until he brings justice to victory.
40原 12:21 And in his name the Gentiles will hope."
40原 12:22 Then they brought to him a demoniac who was blind and mute; and he cured him, so that the one who had been mute could speak and see.
40原 12:23 All the crowds were amazed and said, "Can this be the Son of David?"
40原 12:24 But when the Pharisees heard it, they said, "It is only by Beelzebul, the ruler of the demons, that this fellow casts out the demons."
40原 12:25 He knew what they were thinking and said to them, "Every kingdom divided against itself is laid waste, and no city or house divided against itself will stand.
40原 12:26 If Satan casts out Satan, he is divided against himself; how then will his kingdom stand?
40原 12:27 If I cast out demons by Beelzebul, by whom do your own exorcists cast them out? Therefore they will be your judges.
40原 12:28 But if it is by the Spirit of God that I cast out demons, then the kingdom of God has come to you.
40原 12:29 Or how can one enter a strong man's house and plunder his property, without first tying up the strong man? Then indeed the house can be plundered.
40原 12:30 Whoever is not with me is against me, and whoever does not gather with me scatters.
40原 12:31 Therefore I tell you, people will be forgiven for every sin and blasphemy, but blasphemy against the Spirit will not be forgiven.
40原 12:32 Whoever speaks a word against the Son of Man will be forgiven, but whoever speaks against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven, either in this age or in the age to come.
40原 12:33 "Either make the tree good, and its fruit good; or make the tree bad, and its fruit bad; for the tree is known by its fruit.
40原 12:34 You brood of vipers! How can you speak good things, when you are evil? For out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaks.
40原 12:35 The good person brings good things out of a good treasure, and the evil person brings evil things out of an evil treasure.
40原 12:36 I tell you, on the day of judgment you will have to give an account for every careless word you utter;
40原 12:37 for by your words you will be justified, and by your words you will be condemned."
40原 12:38 Then some of the scribes and Pharisees said to him, "Teacher, we wish to see a sign from you."
40原 12:39 But he answered them, "An evil and adulterous generation asks for a sign, but no sign will be given to it except the sign of the prophet Jonah.
40原 12:40 For just as Jonah was three days and three nights in the belly of the sea monster, so for three days and three nights the Son of Man will be in the heart of the earth.
40原 12:41 The people of Nineveh will rise up at the judgment with this generation and condemn it, because they repented at the proclamation of Jonah, and see, something greater than Jonah is here!
40原 12:42 The queen of the South will rise up at the judgment with this generation and condemn it, because she came from the ends of the earth to listen to the wisdom of Solomon, and see, something greater than Solomon is here!
40原 12:43 "When the unclean spirit has gone out of a person, it wanders through waterless regions looking for a resting place, but it finds none.
40原 12:44 Then it says, 'I will return to my house from which I came.' When it comes, it finds it empty, swept, and put in order.
40原 12:45 Then it goes and brings along seven other spirits more evil than itself, and they enter and live there; and the last state of that person is worse than the first. So will it be also with this evil generation."
40原 12:46 While he was still speaking to the crowds, his mother and his brothers were standing outside, wanting to speak to him.
40原 12:47 Someone told him, "Look, your mother and your brothers are standing outside, wanting to speak to you."
40原 12:48 But to the one who had told him this, Jesus replied, "Who is my mother, and who are my brothers?"
40原 12:49 And pointing to his disciples, he said, "Here are my mother and my brothers!
40原 12:50 For whoever does the will of my Father in heaven is my brother and sister and mother."
40原 13:1 That same day Jesus went out of the house and sat beside the sea.
40原 13:2 Such great crowds gathered around him that he got into a boat and sat there, while the whole crowd stood on the beach.
40原 13:3 And he told them many things in parables, saying: "Listen! A sower went out to sow.
40原 13:4 And as he sowed, some seeds fell on the path, and the birds came and ate them up.
40原 13:5 Other seeds fell on rocky ground, where they did not have much soil, and they sprang up quickly, since they had no depth of soil.
40原 13:6 But when the sun rose, they were scorched; and since they had no root, they withered away.
40原 13:7 Other seeds fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up and choked them.
40原 13:8 Other seeds fell on good soil and brought forth grain, some a hundredfold, some sixty, some thirty.
40原 13:9 Let anyone with ears listen!"
40原 13:10 Then the disciples came and asked him, "Why do you speak to them in parables?"
40原 13:11 He answered, "To you it has been given to know the secrets of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it has not been given.
40原 13:12 For to those who have, more will be given, and they will have an abundance; but from those who have nothing, even what they have will be taken away.
40原 13:13 The reason I speak to them in parables is that 'seeing they do not perceive, and hearing they do not listen, nor do they understand.'
40原 13:14 With them indeed is fulfilled the prophecy of Isaiah that says: 'You will indeed listen, but never understand, and you will indeed look, but never perceive.
40原 13:15 For this people's heart has grown dull, and their ears are hard of hearing, and they have shut their eyes; so that they might not look with their eyes, and listen with their ears, and understand with their heart and turn--and I would heal them.'
40原 13:16 But blessed are your eyes, for they see, and your ears, for they hear.
40原 13:17 Truly I tell you, many prophets and righteous people longed to see what you see, but did not see it, and to hear what you hear, but did not hear it.
40原 13:18 "Hear then the parable of the sower.
40原 13:19 When anyone hears the word of the kingdom and does not understand it, the evil one comes and snatches away what is sown in the heart; this is what was sown on the path.
40原 13:20 As for what was sown on rocky ground, this is the one who hears the word and immediately receives it with joy;
40原 13:21 yet such a person has no root, but endures only for a while, and when trouble or persecution arises on account of the word, that person immediately falls away.
40原 13:22 As for what was sown among thorns, this is the one who hears the word, but the cares of the world and the lure of wealth choke the word, and it yields nothing.
40原 13:23 But as for what was sown on good soil, this is the one who hears the word and understands it, who indeed bears fruit and yields, in one case a hundredfold, in another sixty, and in another thirty."
40原 13:24 He put before them another parable: "The kingdom of heaven may be compared to someone who sowed good seed in his field;
40原 13:25 but while everybody was asleep, an enemy came and sowed weeds among the wheat, and then went away.
40原 13:26 So when the plants came up and bore grain, then the weeds appeared as well.
40原 13:27 And the slaves of the householder came and said to him, 'Master, did you not sow good seed in your field? Where, then, did these weeds come from?'
40原 13:28 He answered, 'An enemy has done this.' The slaves said to him, 'Then do you want us to go and gather them?'
40原 13:29 But he replied, 'No; for in gathering the weeds you would uproot the wheat along with them.
40原 13:30 Let both of them grow together until the harvest; and at harvest time I will tell the reapers, Collect the weeds first and bind them in bundles to be burned, but gather the wheat into my barn.'"
40原 13:31 He put before them another parable: "The kingdom of heaven is like a mustard seed that someone took and sowed in his field;
40原 13:32 it is the smallest of all the seeds, but when it has grown it is the greatest of shrubs and becomes a tree, so that the birds of the air come and make nests in its branches."
40原 13:33 He told them another parable: "The kingdom of heaven is like yeast that a woman took and mixed in with three measures of flour until all of it was leavened."
40原 13:34 Jesus told the crowds all these things in parables; without a parable he told them nothing.
40原 13:35 This was to fulfill what had been spoken through the prophet: "I will open my mouth to speak in parables; I will proclaim what has been hidden from the foundation of the world."
40原 13:36 Then he left the crowds and went into the house. And his disciples approached him, saying, "Explain to us the parable of the weeds of the field."
40原 13:37 He answered, "The one who sows the good seed is the Son of Man;
40原 13:38 the field is the world, and the good seed are the children of the kingdom; the weeds are the children of the evil one,
40原 13:39 and the enemy who sowed them is the devil; the harvest is the end of the age, and the reapers are angels.
40原 13:40 Just as the weeds are collected and burned up with fire, so will it be at the end of the age.
40原 13:41 The Son of Man will send his angels, and they will collect out of his kingdom all causes of sin and all evildoers,
40原 13:42 and they will throw them into the furnace of fire, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
40原 13:43 Then the righteous will shine like the sun in the kingdom of their Father. Let anyone with ears listen!
40原 13:44 "The kingdom of heaven is like treasure hidden in a field, which someone found and hid; then in his joy he goes and sells all that he has and buys that field.
40原 13:45 "Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a merchant in search of fine pearls;
40原 13:46 on finding one pearl of great value, he went and sold all that he had and bought it.
40原 13:47 "Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a net that was thrown into the sea and caught fish of every kind;
40原 13:48 when it was full, they drew it ashore, sat down, and put the good into baskets but threw out the bad.
40原 13:49 So it will be at the end of the age. The angels will come out and separate the evil from the righteous
40原 13:50 and throw them into the furnace of fire, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
40原 13:51 "Have you understood all this?" They answered, "Yes."
40原 13:52 And he said to them, "Therefore every scribe who has been trained for the kingdom of heaven is like the master of a household who brings out of his treasure what is new and what is old."
40原 13:53 When Jesus had finished these parables, he left that place.
40原 13:54 He came to his hometown and began to teach the people in their synagogue, so that they were astounded and said, "Where did this man get this wisdom and these deeds of power?
40原 13:55 Is not this the carpenter's son? Is not his mother called Mary? And are not his brothers James and Joseph and Simon and Judas?
40原 13:56 And are not all his sisters with us? Where then did this man get all this?"
40原 13:57 And they took offense at him. But Jesus said to them, "Prophets are not without honor except in their own country and in their own house."
40原 13:58 And he did not do many deeds of power there, because of their unbelief.
40原 14:1 At that time Herod the ruler heard reports about Jesus;
