40原 14:29 He said, "Come." So Peter got out of the boat, started walking on the water, and came toward Jesus.
40原 14:30 But when he noticed the strong wind, he became frightened, and beginning to sink, he cried out, "Lord, save me!"
40原 14:31 Jesus immediately reached out his hand and caught him, saying to him, "You of little faith, why did you doubt?"
40原 14:32 When they got into the boat, the wind ceased.
40原 14:33 And those in the boat worshiped him, saying, "Truly you are the Son of God."
40原 14:34 When they had crossed over, they came to land at Gennesaret.
40原 14:35 After the people of that place recognized him, they sent word throughout the region and brought all who were sick to him,
40原 14:36 and begged him that they might touch even the fringe of his cloak; and all who touched it were healed.
40原 15:1 Then Pharisees and scribes came to Jesus from Jerusalem and said,
40原 15:2 "Why do your disciples break the tradition of the elders? For they do not wash their hands before they eat."
40原 15:3 He answered them, "And why do you break the commandment of God for the sake of your tradition?
40原 15:4 For God said, 'Honor your father and your mother,' and, 'Whoever speaks evil of father or mother must surely die.'
40原 15:5 But you say that whoever tells father or mother, 'Whatever support you might have had from me is given to God,' then that person need not honor the father.
40原 15:6 So, for the sake of your tradition, you make void the word of God.
40原 15:7 You hypocrites! Isaiah prophesied rightly about you when he said:
40原 15:8 'This people honors me with their lips, but their hearts are far from me;
40原 15:9 in vain do they worship me, teaching human precepts as doctrines.'"
40原 15:10 Then he called the crowd to him and said to them, "Listen and understand:
40原 15:11 it is not what goes into the mouth that defiles a person, but it is what comes out of the mouth that defiles."
40原 15:12 Then the disciples approached and said to him, "Do you know that the Pharisees took offense when they heard what you said?"
40原 15:13 He answered, "Every plant that my heavenly Father has not planted will be uprooted.
40原 15:14 Let them alone; they are blind guides of the blind. And if one blind person guides another, both will fall into a pit."
40原 15:15 But Peter said to him, "Explain this parable to us."
40原 15:16 Then he said, "Are you also still without understanding?
40原 15:17 Do you not see that whatever goes into the mouth enters the stomach, and goes out into the sewer?
40原 15:18 But what comes out of the mouth proceeds from the heart, and this is what defiles.
40原 15:19 For out of the heart come evil intentions, murder, adultery, fornication, theft, false witness, slander.
40原 15:20 These are what defile a person, but to eat with unwashed hands does not defile."
40原 15:21 Jesus left that place and went away to the district of Tyre and Sidon.
40原 15:22 Just then a Canaanite woman from that region came out and started shouting, "Have mercy on me, Lord, Son of David; my daughter is tormented by a demon."
40原 15:23 But he did not answer her at all. And his disciples came and urged him, saying, "Send her away, for she keeps shouting after us."
40原 15:24 He answered, "I was sent only to the lost sheep of the house of Israel."
40原 15:25 But she came and knelt before him, saying, "Lord, help me."
40原 15:26 He answered, "It is not fair to take the children's food and throw it to the dogs."
40原 15:27 She said, "Yes, Lord, yet even the dogs eat the crumbs that fall from their masters' table."
40原 15:28 Then Jesus answered her, "Woman, great is your faith! Let it be done for you as you wish." And her daughter was healed instantly.
40原 15:29 After Jesus had left that place, he passed along the Sea of Galilee, and he went up the mountain, where he sat down.
40原 15:30 Great crowds came to him, bringing with them the lame, the maimed, the blind, the mute, and many others. They put them at his feet, and he cured them,
40原 15:31 so that the crowd was amazed when they saw the mute speaking, the maimed whole, the lame walking, and the blind seeing. And they praised the God of Israel.
40原 15:32 Then Jesus called his disciples to him and said, "I have compassion for the crowd, because they have been with me now for three days and have nothing to eat; and I do not want to send them away hungry, for they might faint on the way."
40原 15:33 The disciples said to him, "Where are we to get enough bread in the desert to feed so great a crowd?"
40原 15:34 Jesus asked them, "How many loaves have you?" They said, "Seven, and a few small fish."
40原 15:35 Then ordering the crowd to sit down on the ground,
40原 15:36 he took the seven loaves and the fish; and after giving thanks he broke them and gave them to the disciples, and the disciples gave them to the crowds.
40原 15:37 And all of them ate and were filled; and they took up the broken pieces left over, seven baskets full.
40原 15:38 Those who had eaten were four thousand men, besides women and children.
40原 15:39 After sending away the crowds, he got into the boat and went to the region of Magadan.
40原 16:1 The Pharisees and Sadducees came, and to test Jesus they asked him to show them a sign from heaven.
40原 16:2 He answered them, "When it is evening, you say, 'It will be fair weather, for the sky is red.'
40原 16:3 And in the morning, 'It will be stormy today, for the sky is red and threatening.' You know how to interpret the appearance of the sky, but you cannot interpret the signs of the times.
40原 16:4 An evil and adulterous generation asks for a sign, but no sign will be given to it except the sign of Jonah." Then he left them and went away.
40原 16:5 When the disciples reached the other side, they had forgotten to bring any bread.
40原 16:6 Jesus said to them, "Watch out, and beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees."
40原 16:7 They said to one another, "It is because we have brought no bread."
40原 16:8 And becoming aware of it, Jesus said, "You of little faith, why are you talking about having no bread?
40原 16:9 Do you still not perceive? Do you not remember the five loaves for the five thousand, and how many baskets you gathered?
40原 16:10 Or the seven loaves for the four thousand, and how many baskets you gathered?
40原 16:11 How could you fail to perceive that I was not speaking about bread? Beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees!"
40原 16:12 Then they understood that he had not told them to beware of the yeast of bread, but of the teaching of the Pharisees and Sadducees.
40原 16:13 Now when Jesus came into the district of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, "Who do people say that the Son of Man is?"
40原 16:14 And they said, "Some say John the Baptist, but others Elijah, and still others Jeremiah or one of the prophets."
40原 16:15 He said to them, "But who do you say that I am?"
40原 16:16 Simon Peter answered, "You are the Messiah, the Son of the living God."
40原 16:17 And Jesus answered him, "Blessed are you, Simon son of Jonah! For flesh and blood has not revealed this to you, but my Father in heaven.
40原 16:18 And I tell you, you are Peter, and on this rock I will build my church, and the gates of Hades will not prevail against it.
40原 16:19 I will give you the keys of the kingdom of heaven, and whatever you bind on earth will be bound in heaven, and whatever you loose on earth will be loosed in heaven."
40原 16:20 Then he sternly ordered the disciples not to tell anyone that he was the Messiah.
40原 16:21 From that time on, Jesus began to show his disciples that he must go to Jerusalem and undergo great suffering at the hands of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and on the third day be raised.
40原 16:22 And Peter took him aside and began to rebuke him, saying, "God forbid it, Lord! This must never happen to you."
40原 16:23 But he turned and said to Peter, "Get behind me, Satan! You are a stumbling block to me; for you are setting your mind not on divine things but on human things."
40原 16:24 Then Jesus told his disciples, "If any want to become my followers, let them deny themselves and take up their cross and follow me.
40原 16:25 For those who want to save their life will lose it, and those who lose their life for my sake will find it.
40原 16:26 For what will it profit them if they gain the whole world but forfeit their life? Or what will they give in return for their life?
40原 16:27 "For the Son of Man is to come with his angels in the glory of his Father, and then he will repay everyone for what has been done.
40原 16:28 Truly I tell you, there are some standing here who will not taste death before they see the Son of Man coming in his kingdom."
40原 17:1 Six days later, Jesus took with him Peter and James and his brother John and led them up a high mountain, by themselves.
40原 17:2 And he was transfigured before them, and his face shone like the sun, and his clothes became dazzling white.
40原 17:3 Suddenly there appeared to them Moses and Elijah, talking with him.
40原 17:4 Then Peter said to Jesus, "Lord, it is good for us to be here; if you wish, I will make three dwellings here, one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."
40原 17:5 While he was still speaking, suddenly a bright cloud overshadowed them, and from the cloud a voice said, "This is my Son, the Beloved; with him I am well pleased; listen to him!"
40原 17:6 When the disciples heard this, they fell to the ground and were overcome by fear.
40原 17:7 But Jesus came and touched them, saying, "Get up and do not be afraid."
40原 17:8 And when they looked up, they saw no one except Jesus himself alone.
40原 17:9 As they were coming down the mountain, Jesus ordered them, "Tell no one about the vision until after the Son of Man has been raised from the dead."
40原 17:10 And the disciples asked him, "Why, then, do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?"
40原 17:11 He replied, "Elijah is indeed coming and will restore all things;
40原 17:12 but I tell you that Elijah has already come, and they did not recognize him, but they did to him whatever they pleased. So also the Son of Man is about to suffer at their hands."
40原 17:13 Then the disciples understood that he was speaking to them about John the Baptist.
40原 17:14 When they came to the crowd, a man came to him, knelt before him,
40原 17:15 and said, "Lord, have mercy on my son, for he is an epileptic and he suffers terribly; he often falls into the fire and often into the water.
40原 17:16 And I brought him to your disciples, but they could not cure him."
40原 17:17 Jesus answered, "You faithless and perverse generation, how much longer must I be with you? How much longer must I put up with you? Bring him here to me."
40原 17:18 And Jesus rebuked the demon, and it came out of him, and the boy was cured instantly.
40原 17:19 Then the disciples came to Jesus privately and said, "Why could we not cast it out?"
40原 17:20 He said to them, "Because of your little faith. For truly I tell you, if you have faith the size of a mustard seed, you will say to this mountain, 'Move from here to there,' and it will move; and nothing will be impossible for you."
40原 17:21 "But this kind does not come out except by prayer and fasting"(貝須)
40原 17:22 As they were gathering in Galilee, Jesus said to them, "The Son of Man is going to be betrayed into human hands,
40原 17:23 and they will kill him, and on the third day he will be raised." And they were greatly distressed.
40原 17:24 When they reached Capernaum, the collectors of the temple tax came to Peter and said, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
40原 17:25 He said, "Yes, he does." And when he came home, Jesus spoke of it first, asking, "What do you think, Simon? From whom do kings of the earth take toll or tribute? From their children or from others?"
40原 17:26 When Peter said, "From others," Jesus said to him, "Then the children are free.
40原 17:27 However, so that we do not give offense to them, go to the sea and cast a hook; take the first fish that comes up; and when you open its mouth, you will find a coin; take that and give it to them for you and me."
40原 18:1 At that time the disciples came to Jesus and asked, "Who is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven?"
40原 18:2 He called a child, whom he put among them,
40原 18:3 and said, "Truly I tell you, unless you change and become like children, you will never enter the kingdom of heaven.
40原 18:4 Whoever becomes humble like this child is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven.
40原 18:5 Whoever welcomes one such child in my name welcomes me.
40原 18:6 "If any of you put a stumbling block before one of these little ones who believe in me, it would be better for you if a great millstone were fastened around your neck and you were drowned in the depth of the sea.
40原 18:7 Woe to the world because of stumbling blocks! Occasions for stumbling are bound to come, but woe to the one by whom the stumbling block comes!
40原 18:8 "If your hand or your foot causes you to stumble, cut it off and throw it away; it is better for you to enter life maimed or lame than to have two hands or two feet and to be thrown into the eternal fire.
40原 18:9 And if your eye causes you to stumble, tear it out and throw it away; it is better for you to enter life with one eye than to have two eyes and to be thrown into the hell of fire.
40原 18:10 "Take care that you do not despise one of these little ones; for, I tell you, in heaven their angels continually see the face of my Father in heaven.
40原 18:11 For the Son of Man came to save the lost.(貝須)
40原 18:12 What do you think? If a shepherd has a hundred sheep, and one of them has gone astray, does he not leave the ninety-nine on the mountains and go in search of the one that went astray?
40原 18:13 And if he finds it, truly I tell you, he rejoices over it more than over the ninety-nine that never went astray.
40原 18:14 So it is not the will of your Father in heaven that one of these little ones should be lost.
40原 18:15 "If another member of the church sins against you, go and point out the fault when the two of you are alone. If the member listens to you, you have regained that one.
40原 18:16 But if you are not listened to, take one or two others along with you, so that every word may be confirmed by the evidence of two or three witnesses.
40原 18:17 If the member refuses to listen to them, tell it to the church; and if the offender refuses to listen even to the church, let such a one be to you as a Gentile and a tax collector.
40原 18:18 Truly I tell you, whatever you bind on earth will be bound in heaven, and whatever you loose on earth will be loosed in heaven.
40原 18:19 Again, truly I tell you, if two of you agree on earth about anything you ask, it will be done for you by my Father in heaven.
40原 18:20 For where two or three are gathered in my name, I am there among them."
40原 18:21 Then Peter came and said to him, "Lord, if another member of the church sins against me, how often should I forgive? As many as seven times?"
40原 18:22 Jesus said to him, "Not seven times, but, I tell you, seventy-seven times.
40原 18:23 "For this reason the kingdom of heaven may be compared to a king who wished to settle accounts with his slaves.
40原 18:24 When he began the reckoning, one who owed him ten thousand talents was brought to him;
40原 18:25 and, as he could not pay, his lord ordered him to be sold, together with his wife and children and all his possessions, and payment to be made.
40原 18:26 So the slave fell on his knees before him, saying, 'Have patience with me, and I will pay you everything.'
40原 18:27 And out of pity for him, the lord of that slave released him and forgave him the debt.
40原 18:28 But that same slave, as he went out, came upon one of his fellow slaves who owed him a hundred denarii; and seizing him by the throat, he said, 'Pay what you owe.'
40原 18:29 Then his fellow slave fell down and pleaded with him, 'Have patience with me, and I will pay you.'
40原 18:30 But he refused; then he went and threw him into prison until he would pay the debt.
40原 18:31 When his fellow slaves saw what had happened, they were greatly distressed, and they went and reported to their lord all that had taken place.
40原 18:32 Then his lord summoned him and said to him, 'You wicked slave! I forgave you all that debt because you pleaded with me.
40原 18:33 Should you not have had mercy on your fellow slave, as I had mercy on you?'
40原 18:34 And in anger his lord handed him over to be tortured until he would pay his entire debt.
40原 18:35 So my heavenly Father will also do to every one of you, if you do not forgive your brother or sister from your heart."
40原 19:1 When Jesus had finished saying these things, he left Galilee and went to the region of Judea beyond the Jordan.
40原 19:2 Large crowds followed him, and he cured them there.
40原 19:3 Some Pharisees came to him, and to test him they asked, "Is it lawful for a man to divorce his wife for any cause?"
40原 19:4 He answered, "Have you not read that the one who made them at the beginning 'made them male and female,'
40原 19:5 and said, 'For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and the two shall become one flesh'?
40原 19:6 So they are no longer two, but one flesh. Therefore what God has joined together, let no one separate."
40原 19:7 They said to him, "Why then did Moses command us to give a certificate of dismissal and to divorce her?"
40原 19:8 He said to them, "It was because you were so hard-hearted that Moses allowed you to divorce your wives, but from the beginning it was not so.
40原 19:9 And I say to you, whoever divorces his wife, except for unchastity, and marries another commits adultery."
40原 19:10 His disciples said to him, "If such is the case of a man with his wife, it is better not to marry."
40原 19:11 But he said to them, "Not everyone can accept this teaching, but only those to whom it is given.
40原 19:12 For there are eunuchs who have been so from birth, and there are eunuchs who have been made eunuchs by others, and there are eunuchs who have made themselves eunuchs for the sake of the kingdom of heaven. Let anyone accept this who can."
40原 19:13 Then little children were being brought to him in order that he might lay his hands on them and pray. The disciples spoke sternly to those who brought them;
40原 19:14 but Jesus said, "Let the little children come to me, and do not stop them; for it is to such as these that the kingdom of heaven belongs."
40原 19:15 And he laid his hands on them and went on his way.
40原 19:16 Then someone came to him and said, "Teacher, what good deed must I do to have eternal life?"
40原 19:17 And he said to him, "Why do you ask me about what is good? There is only one who is good. If you wish to enter into life, keep the commandments."
40原 19:18 He said to him, "Which ones?" And Jesus said, "You shall not murder; You shall not commit adultery; You shall not steal; You shall not bear false witness;
40原 19:19 Honor your father and mother; also, You shall love your neighbor as yourself."
40原 19:20 The young man said to him, "I have kept all these; what do I still lack?"
40原 19:21 Jesus said to him, "If you wish to be perfect, go, sell your possessions, and give the money to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven; then come, follow me."
40原 19:22 When the young man heard this word, he went away grieving, for he had many possessions.
40原 19:23 Then Jesus said to his disciples, "Truly I tell you, it will be hard for a rich person to enter the kingdom of heaven.
40原 19:24 Again I tell you, it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for someone who is rich to enter the kingdom of God."
40原 19:25 When the disciples heard this, they were greatly astounded and said, "Then who can be saved?"
40原 19:26 But Jesus looked at them and said, "For mortals it is impossible, but for God all things are possible."
40原 19:27 Then Peter said in reply, "Look, we have left everything and followed you. What then will we have?"
40原 19:28 Jesus said to them, "Truly I tell you, at the renewal of all things, when the Son of Man is seated on the throne of his glory, you who have followed me will also sit on twelve thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
40原 19:29 And everyone who has left houses or brothers or sisters or father or mother or children or fields, for my name's sake, will receive a hundredfold, and will inherit eternal life.
40原 19:30 But many who are first will be last, and the last will be first.
40原 20:1 "For the kingdom of heaven is like a landowner who went out early in the morning to hire laborers for his vineyard.
40原 20:2 After agreeing with the laborers for the usual daily wage, he sent them into his vineyard.
40原 20:3 When he went out about nine o'clock, he saw others standing idle in the marketplace;
40原 20:4 and he said to them, 'You also go into the vineyard, and I will pay you whatever is right.' So they went.
40原 20:5 When he went out again about noon and about three o'clock, he did the same.
40原 20:6 And about five o'clock he went out and found others standing around; and he said to them, 'Why are you standing here idle all day?'
40原 20:7 They said to him, 'Because no one has hired us.' He said to them, 'You also go into the vineyard.'
40原 20:8 When evening came, the owner of the vineyard said to his manager, 'Call the laborers and give them their pay, beginning with the last and then going to the first.'
40原 20:9 When those hired about five o'clock came, each of them received the usual daily wage.
40原 20:10 Now when the first came, they thought they would receive more; but each of them also received the usual daily wage.
40原 20:11 And when they received it, they grumbled against the landowner,
40原 20:12 saying, 'These last worked only one hour, and you have made them equal to us who have borne the burden of the day and the scorching heat.'
40原 20:13 But he replied to one of them, 'Friend, I am doing you no wrong; did you not agree with me for the usual daily wage?
40原 20:14 Take what belongs to you and go; I choose to give to this last the same as I give to you.
40原 20:15 Am I not allowed to do what I choose with what belongs to me? Or are you envious because I am generous?'
40原 20:16 So the last will be first, and the first will be last."
40原 20:17 While Jesus was going up to Jerusalem, he took the twelve disciples aside by themselves, and said to them on the way,
40原 20:18 "See, we are going up to Jerusalem, and the Son of Man will be handed over to the chief priests and scribes, and they will condemn him to death;
40原 20:19 then they will hand him over to the Gentiles to be mocked and flogged and crucified; and on the third day he will be raised."
40原 20:20 Then the mother of the sons of Zebedee came to him with her sons, and kneeling before him, she asked a favor of him.
40原 20:21 And he said to her, "What do you want?" She said to him, "Declare that these two sons of mine will sit, one at your right hand and one at your left, in your kingdom."
40原 20:22 But Jesus answered, "You do not know what you are asking. Are you able to drink the cup that I am about to drink?" They said to him, "We are able."
40原 20:23 He said to them, "You will indeed drink my cup, but to sit at my right hand and at my left, this is not mine to grant, but it is for those for whom it has been prepared by my Father."
40原 20:24 When the ten heard it, they were angry with the two brothers.
40原 20:25 But Jesus called them to him and said, "You know that the rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them, and their great ones are tyrants over them.
40原 20:26 It will not be so among you; but whoever wishes to be great among you must be your servant,
40原 20:27 and whoever wishes to be first among you must be your slave;
40原 20:28 just as the Son of Man came not to be served but to serve, and to give his life a ransom for many."
40原 20:29 As they were leaving Jericho, a large crowd followed him.
40原 20:30 There were two blind men sitting by the roadside. When they heard that Jesus was passing by, they shouted, "Lord, have mercy on us, Son of David!"
40原 20:31 The crowd sternly ordered them to be quiet; but they shouted even more loudly, "Have mercy on us, Lord, Son of David!"
40原 20:32 Jesus stood still and called them, saying, "What do you want me to do for you?"
40原 20:33 They said to him, "Lord, let our eyes be opened."
40原 20:34 Moved with compassion, Jesus touched their eyes. Immediately they regained their sight and followed him.
40原 21:1 When they had come near Jerusalem and had reached Bethphage, at the Mount of Olives, Jesus sent two disciples,
40原 21:2 saying to them, "Go into the village ahead of you, and immediately you will find a donkey tied, and a colt with her; untie them and bring them to me.
40原 21:3 If anyone says anything to you, just say this, 'The Lord needs them.' And he will send them immediately."
40原 21:4 This took place to fulfill what had been spoken through the prophet, saying,
40原 21:5 "Tell the daughter of Zion, Look, your king is coming to you, humble, and mounted on a donkey, and on a colt, the foal of a donkey."
40原 21:6 The disciples went and did as Jesus had directed them;
40原 21:7 they brought the donkey and the colt, and put their cloaks on them, and he sat on them.
40原 21:8 A very large crowd spread their cloaks on the road, and others cut branches from the trees and spread them on the road.
40原 21:9 The crowds that went ahead of him and that followed were shouting, "Hosanna to the Son of David! Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord! Hosanna in the highest heaven!"
40原 21:10 When he entered Jerusalem, the whole city was in turmoil, asking, "Who is this?"
40原 21:11 The crowds were saying, "This is the prophet Jesus from Nazareth in Galilee."
40原 21:12 Then Jesus entered the temple and drove out all who were selling and buying in the temple, and he overturned the tables of the money changers and the seats of those who sold doves.
40原 21:13 He said to them, "It is written, 'My house shall be called a house of prayer'; but you are making it a den of robbers."
40原 21:14 The blind and the lame came to him in the temple, and he cured them.
40原 21:15 But when the chief priests and the scribes saw the amazing things that he did, and heard the children crying out in the temple, "Hosanna to the Son of David," they became angry
40原 21:16 and said to him, "Do you hear what these are saying?" Jesus said to them, "Yes; have you never read, 'Out of the mouths of infants and nursing babies you have prepared praise for yourself'?"
40原 21:17 He left them, went out of the city to Bethany, and spent the night there.
40原 21:18 In the morning, when he returned to the city, he was hungry.
40原 21:19 And seeing a fig tree by the side of the road, he went to it and found nothing at all on it but leaves. Then he said to it, "May no fruit ever come from you again!" And the fig tree withered at once.
40原 21:20 When the disciples saw it, they were amazed, saying, "How did the fig tree wither at once?"
40原 21:21 Jesus answered them, "Truly I tell you, if you have faith and do not doubt, not only will you do what has been done to the fig tree, but even if you say to this mountain, 'Be lifted up and thrown into the sea,' it will be done.
40原 21:22 Whatever you ask for in prayer with faith, you will receive."
40原 21:23 When he entered the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came to him as he was teaching, and said, "By what authority are you doing these things, and who gave you this authority?"
40原 21:24 Jesus said to them, "I will also ask you one question; if you tell me the answer, then I will also tell you by what authority I do these things.
40原 21:25 Did the baptism of John come from heaven, or was it of human origin?" And they argued with one another, "If we say, 'From heaven,' he will say to us, 'Why then did you not believe him?'
40原 21:26 But if we say, 'Of human origin,' we are afraid of the crowd; for all regard John as a prophet."
40原 21:27 So they answered Jesus, "We do not know." And he said to them, "Neither will I tell you by what authority I am doing these things.
40原 21:28 "What do you think? A man had two sons; he went to the first and said, 'Son, go and work in the vineyard today.'
40原 21:29 He answered, 'I will not'; but later he changed his mind and went.
40原 21:30 The father went to the second and said the same; and he answered, 'I go, sir'; but he did not go.
40原 21:31 Which of the two did the will of his father?" They said, "The first." Jesus said to them, "Truly I tell you, the tax collectors and the prostitutes are going into the kingdom of God ahead of you.
40原 21:32 For John came to you in the way of righteousness and you did not believe him, but the tax collectors and the prostitutes believed him; and even after you saw it, you did not change your minds and believe him.
40原 21:33 "Listen to another parable. There was a landowner who planted a vineyard, put a fence around it, dug a wine press in it, and built a watchtower. Then he leased it to tenants and went to another country.
40原 21:34 When the harvest time had come, he sent his slaves to the tenants to collect his produce.
40原 21:35 But the tenants seized his slaves and beat one, killed another, and stoned another.
40原 21:36 Again he sent other slaves, more than the first; and they treated them in the same way.
40原 21:37 Finally he sent his son to them, saying, 'They will respect my son.'
40原 21:38 But when the tenants saw the son, they said to themselves, 'This is the heir; come, let us kill him and get his inheritance.'
40原 21:39 So they seized him, threw him out of the vineyard, and killed him.
40原 21:40 Now when the owner of the vineyard comes, what will he do to those tenants?"
40原 21:41 They said to him, "He will put those wretches to a miserable death, and lease the vineyard to other tenants who will give him the produce at the harvest time."
40原 21:42 Jesus said to them, "Have you never read in the scriptures: 'The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone; this was the Lord's doing, and it is amazing in our eyes'?
40原 21:43 Therefore I tell you, the kingdom of God will be taken away from you and given to a people that produces the fruits of the kingdom.
40原 21:44 The one who falls on this stone will be broken to pieces; and it will crush anyone on whom it falls."
40原 21:45 When the chief priests and the Pharisees heard his parables, they realized that he was speaking about them.
40原 21:46 They wanted to arrest him, but they feared the crowds, because they regarded him as a prophet.
40原 22:1 Once more Jesus spoke to them in parables, saying:
40原 22:2 "The kingdom of heaven may be compared to a king who gave a wedding banquet for his son.
40原 22:3 He sent his slaves to call those who had been invited to the wedding banquet, but they would not come.
40原 22:4 Again he sent other slaves, saying, 'Tell those who have been invited: Look, I have prepared my dinner, my oxen and my fat calves have been slaughtered, and everything is ready; come to the wedding banquet.'
40原 22:5 But they made light of it and went away, one to his farm, another to his business,
40原 22:6 while the rest seized his slaves, mistreated them, and killed them.
40原 22:7 The king was enraged. He sent his troops, destroyed those murderers, and burned their city.
40原 22:8 Then he said to his slaves, 'The wedding is ready, but those invited were not worthy.
40原 22:9 Go therefore into the main streets, and invite everyone you find to the wedding banquet.'
40原 22:10 Those slaves went out into the streets and gathered all whom they found, both good and bad; so the wedding hall was filled with guests.
40原 22:11 "But when the king came in to see the guests, he noticed a man there who was not wearing a wedding robe,
40原 22:12 and he said to him, 'Friend, how did you get in here without a wedding robe?' And he was speechless.
40原 22:13 Then the king said to the attendants, 'Bind him hand and foot, and throw him into the outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'
40原 22:14 For many are called, but few are chosen."
40原 22:15 Then the Pharisees went and plotted to entrap him in what he said.
40原 22:16 So they sent their disciples to him, along with the Herodians, saying, "Teacher, we know that you are sincere, and teach the way of God in accordance with truth, and show deference to no one; for you do not regard people with partiality.
40原 22:17 Tell us, then, what you think. Is it lawful to pay taxes to the emperor, or not?"
40原 22:18 But Jesus, aware of their malice, said, "Why are you putting me to the test, you hypocrites?
40原 22:19 Show me the coin used for the tax." And they brought him a denarius.
40原 22:20 Then he said to them, "Whose head is this, and whose title?"
40原 22:21 They answered, "The emperor's." Then he said to them, "Give therefore to the emperor the things that are the emperor's, and to God the things that are God's."
40原 22:22 When they heard this, they were amazed; and they left him and went away.
40原 22:23 The same day some Sadducees came to him, saying there is no resurrection; and they asked him a question, saying,
40原 22:24 "Teacher, Moses said, 'If a man dies childless, his brother shall marry the widow, and raise up children for his brother.'
40原 22:25 Now there were seven brothers among us; the first married, and died childless, leaving the widow to his brother.
40原 22:26 The second did the same, so also the third, down to the seventh.
40原 22:27 Last of all, the woman herself died.
40原 22:28 In the resurrection, then, whose wife of the seven will she be? For all of them had married her."
40原 22:29 Jesus answered them, "You are wrong, because you know neither the scriptures nor the power of God.
40原 22:30 For in the resurrection they neither marry nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.
40原 22:31 And as for the resurrection of the dead, have you not read what was said to you by God,
40原 22:32 'I am the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob'? He is God not of the dead, but of the living."
40原 22:33 And when the crowd heard it, they were astounded at his teaching.
40原 22:34 When the Pharisees heard that he had silenced the Sadducees, they gathered together,
40原 22:35 and one of them, a lawyer, asked him a question to test him.
40原 22:36 "Teacher, which commandment in the law is the greatest?"
40原 22:37 He said to him, "'You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind.'
40原 22:38 This is the greatest and first commandment.
40原 22:39 And a second is like it: 'You shall love your neighbor as yourself.'
40原 22:40 On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets."
40原 22:41 Now while the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them this question:
40原 22:42 "What do you think of the Messiah? Whose son is he?" They said to him, "The son of David."
40原 22:43 He said to them, "How is it then that David by the Spirit calls him Lord, saying,
40原 22:44 'The Lord said to my Lord, "Sit at my right hand, until I put your enemies under your feet"'?
40原 22:45 If David thus calls him Lord, how can he be his son?"
40原 22:46 No one was able to give him an answer, nor from that day did anyone dare to ask him any more questions.
40原 23:1 Then Jesus said to the crowds and to his disciples,
40原 23:2 "The scribes and the Pharisees sit on Moses' seat;
40原 23:3 therefore, do whatever they teach you and follow it; but do not do as they do, for they do not practice what they teach.
40原 23:4 They tie up heavy burdens, hard to bear, and lay them on the shoulders of others; but they themselves are unwilling to lift a finger to move them.
40原 23:5 They do all their deeds to be seen by others; for they make their phylacteries broad and their fringes long.
40原 23:6 They love to have the place of honor at banquets and the best seats in the synagogues,
40原 23:7 and to be greeted with respect in the marketplaces, and to have people call them rabbi.
40原 23:8 But you are not to be called rabbi, for you have one teacher, and you are all students.
40原 23:9 And call no one your father on earth, for you have one Father--the one in heaven.
40原 23:10 Nor are you to be called instructors, for you have one instructor, the Messiah.
40原 23:11 The greatest among you will be your servant.
40原 23:12 All who exalt themselves will be humbled, and all who humble themselves will be exalted.
40原 23:13 "But woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you lock people out of the kingdom of heaven. For you do not go in yourselves, and when others are going in, you stop them.
40原 23:14 Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you devour widow' houses and for the sake of appearance you make long prayers; therefore you will receive the greater condemnation.(貝須)
40原 23:15 Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you cross sea and land to make a single convert, and you make the new convert twice as much a child of hell as yourselves.
40原 23:16 "Woe to you, blind guides, who say, 'Whoever swears by the sanctuary is bound by nothing, but whoever swears by the gold of the sanctuary is bound by the oath.'
40原 23:17 You blind fools! For which is greater, the gold or the sanctuary that has made the gold sacred?
40原 23:18 And you say, 'Whoever swears by the altar is bound by nothing, but whoever swears by the gift that is on the altar is bound by the oath.'
40原 23:19 How blind you are! For which is greater, the gift or the altar that makes the gift sacred?
40原 23:20 So whoever swears by the altar, swears by it and by everything on it;
40原 23:21 and whoever swears by the sanctuary, swears by it and by the one who dwells in it;
40原 23:22 and whoever swears by heaven, swears by the throne of God and by the one who is seated upon it.
40原 23:23 "Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you tithe mint, dill, and cummin, and have neglected the weightier matters of the law: justice and mercy and faith. It is these you ought to have practiced without neglecting the others.
40原 23:24 You blind guides! You strain out a gnat but swallow a camel!
40原 23:25 "Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you clean the outside of the cup and of the plate, but inside they are full of greed and self-indulgence.
40原 23:26 You blind Pharisee! First clean the inside of the cup, so that the outside also may become clean.
40原 23:27 "Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you are like whitewashed tombs, which on the outside look beautiful, but inside they are full of the bones of the dead and of all kinds of filth.
40原 23:28 So you also on the outside look righteous to others, but inside you are full of hypocrisy and lawlessness.
40原 23:29 "Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! For you build the tombs of the prophets and decorate the graves of the righteous,
40原 23:30 and you say, 'If we had lived in the days of our ancestors, we would not have taken part with them in shedding the blood of the prophets.'
40原 23:31 Thus you testify against yourselves that you are descendants of those who murdered the prophets.
40原 23:32 Fill up, then, the measure of your ancestors.
40原 23:33 You snakes, you brood of vipers! How can you escape being sentenced to hell?
40原 23:34 Therefore I send you prophets, sages, and scribes, some of whom you will kill and crucify, and some you will flog in your synagogues and pursue from town to town,
40原 23:35 so that upon you may come all the righteous blood shed on earth, from the blood of righteous Abel to the blood of Zechariah son of Barachiah, whom you murdered between the sanctuary and the altar.
40原 23:36 Truly I tell you, all this will come upon this generation.
40原 23:37 "Jerusalem, Jerusalem, the city that kills the prophets and stones those who are sent to it! How often have I desired to gather your children together as a hen gathers her brood under her wings, and you were not willing!
40原 23:38 See, your house is left to you, desolate.
40原 23:39 For I tell you, you will not see me again until you say, 'Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord.'"
40原 24:1 As Jesus came out of the temple and was going away, his disciples came to point out to him the buildings of the temple.
40原 24:2 Then he asked them, "You see all these, do you not? Truly I tell you, not one stone will be left here upon another; all will be thrown down."
40原 24:3 When he was sitting on the Mount of Olives, the disciples came to him privately, saying, "Tell us, when will this be, and what will be the sign of your coming and of the end of the age?"
40原 24:4 Jesus answered them, "Beware that no one leads you astray.
40原 24:5 For many will come in my name, saying, 'I am the Messiah!' and they will lead many astray.
40原 24:6 And you will hear of wars and rumors of wars; see that you are not alarmed; for this must take place, but the end is not yet.
40原 24:7 For nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom, and there will be famines and earthquakes in various places:
40原 24:8 all this is but the beginning of the birthpangs.
40原 24:9 "Then they will hand you over to be tortured and will put you to death, and you will be hated by all nations because of my name.
40原 24:10 Then many will fall away, and they will betray one another and hate one another.
40原 24:11 And many false prophets will arise and lead many astray.
40原 24:12 And because of the increase of lawlessness, the love of many will grow cold.
40原 24:13 But the one who endures to the end will be saved.
40原 24:14 And this good news of the kingdom will be proclaimed throughout the world, as a testimony to all the nations; and then the end will come.
40原 24:15 "So when you see the desolating sacrilege standing in the holy place, as was spoken of by the prophet Daniel (let the reader understand),
40原 24:16 then those in Judea must flee to the mountains;
40原 24:17 the one on the housetop must not go down to take what is in the house;
40原 24:18 the one in the field must not turn back to get a coat.
40原 24:19 Woe to those who are pregnant and to those who are nursing infants in those days!
40原 24:20 Pray that your flight may not be in winter or on a sabbath.
40原 24:21 For at that time there will be great suffering, such as has not been from the beginning of the world until now, no, and never will be.
40原 24:22 And if those days had not been cut short, no one would be saved; but for the sake of the elect those days will be cut short.
40原 24:23 Then if anyone says to you, 'Look! Here is the Messiah!' or 'There he is!'--do not believe it.
40原 24:24 For false messiahs and false prophets will appear and produce great signs and omens, to lead astray, if possible, even the elect.
40原 24:25 Take note, I have told you beforehand.
40原 24:26 So, if they say to you, 'Look! He is in the wilderness,' do not go out. If they say, 'Look! He is in the inner rooms,' do not believe it.
40原 24:27 For as the lightning comes from the east and flashes as far as the west, so will be the coming of the Son of Man.
40原 24:28 Wherever the corpse is, there the vultures will gather.
40原 24:29 "Immediately after the suffering of those days the sun will be darkened, and the moon will not give its light; the stars will fall from heaven, and the powers of heaven will be shaken.
40原 24:30 Then the sign of the Son of Man will appear in heaven, and then all the tribes of the earth will mourn, and they will see 'the Son of Man coming on the clouds of heaven' with power and great glory.
40原 24:31 And he will send out his angels with a loud trumpet call, and they will gather his elect from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other.
40原 24:32 "From the fig tree learn its lesson: as soon as its branch becomes tender and puts forth its leaves, you know that summer is near.
40原 24:33 So also, when you see all these things, you know that he is near, at the very gates.
40原 24:34 Truly I tell you, this generation will not pass away until all these things have taken place.
40原 24:35 Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.
40原 24:36 "But about that day and hour no one knows, neither the angels of heaven, nor the Son, but only the Father.
40原 24:37 For as the days of Noah were, so will be the coming of the Son of Man.
40原 24:38 For as in those days before the flood they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the day Noah entered the ark,
40原 24:39 and they knew nothing until the flood came and swept them all away, so too will be the coming of the Son of Man.
40原 24:40 Then two will be in the field; one will be taken and one will be left.
40原 24:41 Two women will be grinding meal together; one will be taken and one will be left.
40原 24:42 Keep awake therefore, for you do not know on what day your Lord is coming.
40原 24:43 But understand this: if the owner of the house had known in what part of the night the thief was coming, he would have stayed awake and would not have let his house be broken into.
40原 24:44 Therefore you also must be ready, for the Son of Man is coming at an unexpected hour.
40原 24:45 "Who then is the faithful and wise slave, whom his master has put in charge of his household, to give the other slaves their allowance of food at the proper time?
40原 24:46 Blessed is that slave whom his master will find at work when he arrives.
40原 24:47 Truly I tell you, he will put that one in charge of all his possessions.
40原 24:48 But if that wicked slave says to himself, 'My master is delayed,'
40原 24:49 and he begins to beat his fellow slaves, and eats and drinks with drunkards,
40原 24:50 the master of that slave will come on a day when he does not expect him and at an hour that he does not know.
40原 24:51 He will cut him in pieces and put him with the hypocrites, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
40原 25:1 "Then the kingdom of heaven will be like this. Ten bridesmaids took their lamps and went to meet the bridegroom.
40原 25:2 Five of them were foolish, and five were wise.
40原 25:3 When the foolish took their lamps, they took no oil with them;
40原 25:4 but the wise took flasks of oil with their lamps.
40原 25:5 As the bridegroom was delayed, all of them became drowsy and slept.
40原 25:6 But at midnight there was a shout, 'Look! Here is the bridegroom! Come out to meet him.'
40原 25:7 Then all those bridesmaids got up and trimmed their lamps.
40原 25:8 The foolish said to the wise, 'Give us some of your oil, for our lamps are going out.'
40原 25:9 But the wise replied, 'No! there will not be enough for you and for us; you had better go to the dealers and buy some for yourselves.'
40原 25:10 And while they went to buy it, the bridegroom came, and those who were ready went with him into the wedding banquet; and the door was shut.
40原 25:11 Later the other bridesmaids came also, saying, 'Lord, lord, open to us.'
40原 25:12 But he replied, 'Truly I tell you, I do not know you.'
40原 25:13 Keep awake therefore, for you know neither the day nor the hour.
40原 25:14 "For it is as if a man, going on a journey, summoned his slaves and entrusted his property to them;
40原 25:15 to one he gave five talents, to another two, to another one, to each according to his ability. Then he went away.
40原 25:16 The one who had received the five talents went off at once and traded with them, and made five more talents.
40原 25:17 In the same way, the one who had the two talents made two more talents.
40原 25:18 But the one who had received the one talent went off and dug a hole in the ground and hid his master's money.
40原 25:19 After a long time the master of those slaves came and settled accounts with them.
40原 25:20 Then the one who had received the five talents came forward, bringing five more talents, saying, 'Master, you handed over to me five talents; see, I have made five more talents.'
40原 25:21 His master said to him, 'Well done, good and trustworthy slave; you have been trustworthy in a few things, I will put you in charge of many things; enter into the joy of your master.'
40原 25:22 And the one with the two talents also came forward, saying, 'Master, you handed over to me two talents; see, I have made two more talents.'
40原 25:23 His master said to him, 'Well done, good and trustworthy slave; you have been trustworthy in a few things, I will put you in charge of many things; enter into the joy of your master.'
40原 25:24 Then the one who had received the one talent also came forward, saying, 'Master, I knew that you were a harsh man, reaping where you did not sow, and gathering where you did not scatter seed;
40原 25:25 so I was afraid, and I went and hid your talent in the ground. Here you have what is yours.'
40原 25:26 But his master replied, 'You wicked and lazy slave! You knew, did you, that I reap where I did not sow, and gather where I did not scatter?
40原 25:27 Then you ought to have invested my money with the bankers, and on my return I would have received what was my own with interest.
40原 25:28 So take the talent from him, and give it to the one with the ten talents.
40原 25:29 For to all those who have, more will be given, and they will have an abundance; but from those who have nothing, even what they have will be taken away.
40原 25:30 As for this worthless slave, throw him into the outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'
40原 25:31 "When the Son of Man comes in his glory, and all the angels with him, then he will sit on the throne of his glory.
40原 25:32 All the nations will be gathered before him, and he will separate people one from another as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats,
40原 25:33 and he will put the sheep at his right hand and the goats at the left.
40原 25:34 Then the king will say to those at his right hand, 'Come, you that are blessed by my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world;
40原 25:35 for I was hungry and you gave me food, I was thirsty and you gave me something to drink, I was a stranger and you welcomed me,
40原 25:36 I was naked and you gave me clothing, I was sick and you took care of me, I was in prison and you visited me.'
40原 25:37 Then the righteous will answer him, 'Lord, when was it that we saw you hungry and gave you food, or thirsty and gave you something to drink?
40原 25:38 And when was it that we saw you a stranger and welcomed you, or naked and gave you clothing?
40原 25:39 And when was it that we saw you sick or in prison and visited you?'
40原 25:40 And the king will answer them, 'Truly I tell you, just as you did it to one of the least of these who are members of my family, you did it to me.'
40原 25:41 Then he will say to those at his left hand, 'You that are accursed, depart from me into the eternal fire prepared for the devil and his angels;
40原 25:42 for I was hungry and you gave me no food, I was thirsty and you gave me nothing to drink,
40原 25:43 I was a stranger and you did not welcome me, naked and you did not give me clothing, sick and in prison and you did not visit me.'
40原 25:44 Then they also will answer, 'Lord, when was it that we saw you hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison, and did not take care of you?'
40原 25:45 Then he will answer them, 'Truly I tell you, just as you did not do it to one of the least of these, you did not do it to me.'
40原 25:46 And these will go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal life."
40原 26:1 When Jesus had finished saying all these things, he said to his disciples,
40原 26:2 "You know that after two days the Passover is coming, and the Son of Man will be handed over to be crucified."
40原 26:3 Then the chief priests and the elders of the people gathered in the palace of the high priest, who was called Caiaphas,
40原 26:4 and they conspired to arrest Jesus by stealth and kill him.
40原 26:5 But they said, "Not during the festival, or there may be a riot among the people."
40原 26:6 Now while Jesus was at Bethany in the house of Simon the leper,
40原 26:7 a woman came to him with an alabaster jar of very costly ointment, and she poured it on his head as he sat at the table.
40原 26:8 But when the disciples saw it, they were angry and said, "Why this waste?
40原 26:9 For this ointment could have been sold for a large sum, and the money given to the poor."
40原 26:10 But Jesus, aware of this, said to them, "Why do you trouble the woman? She has performed a good service for me.
40原 26:11 For you always have the poor with you, but you will not always have me.
40原 26:12 By pouring this ointment on my body she has prepared me for burial.
40原 26:13 Truly I tell you, wherever this good news is proclaimed in the whole world, what she has done will be told in remembrance of her."
40原 26:14 Then one of the twelve, who was called Judas Iscariot, went to the chief priests
40原 26:15 and said, "What will you give me if I betray him to you?" They paid him thirty pieces of silver.
40原 26:16 And from that moment he began to look for an opportunity to betray him.
40原 26:17 On the first day of Unleavened Bread the disciples came to Jesus, saying, "Where do you want us to make the preparations for you to eat the Passover?"
40原 26:18 He said, "Go into the city to a certain man, and say to him, 'The Teacher says, My time is near; I will keep the Passover at your house with my disciples.'"
40原 26:19 So the disciples did as Jesus had directed them, and they prepared the Passover meal.
40原 26:20 When it was evening, he took his place with the twelve;
40原 26:21 and while they were eating, he said, "Truly I tell you, one of you will betray me."
40原 26:22 And they became greatly distressed and began to say to him one after another, "Surely not I, Lord?"
40原 26:23 He answered, "The one who has dipped his hand into the bowl with me will betray me.
40原 26:24 The Son of Man goes as it is written of him, but woe to that one by whom the Son of Man is betrayed! It would have been better for that one not to have been born."
40原 26:25 Judas, who betrayed him, said, "Surely not I, Rabbi?" He replied, "You have said so."
40原 26:26 While they were eating, Jesus took a loaf of bread, and after blessing it he broke it, gave it to the disciples, and said, "Take, eat; this is my body."
40原 26:27 Then he took a cup, and after giving thanks he gave it to them, saying, "Drink from it, all of you;
40原 26:28 for this is my blood of the covenant, which is poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins.
40原 26:29 I tell you, I will never again drink of this fruit of the vine until that day when I drink it new with you in my Father's kingdom."
40原 26:30 When they had sung the hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.
40原 26:31 Then Jesus said to them, "You will all become deserters because of me this night; for it is written, 'I will strike the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.'
40原 26:32 But after I am raised up, I will go ahead of you to Galilee."
40原 26:33 Peter said to him, "Though all become deserters because of you, I will never desert you."
40原 26:34 Jesus said to him, "Truly I tell you, this very night, before the cock crows, you will deny me three times."
40原 26:35 Peter said to him, "Even though I must die with you, I will not deny you." And so said all the disciples.
40原 26:36 Then Jesus went with them to a place called Gethsemane; and he said to his disciples, "Sit here while I go over there and pray."
40原 26:37 He took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, and began to be grieved and agitated.
40原 26:38 Then he said to them, "I am deeply grieved, even to death; remain here, and stay awake with me."
40原 26:39 And going a little farther, he threw himself on the ground and prayed, "My Father, if it is possible, let this cup pass from me; yet not what I want but what you want."
40原 26:40 Then he came to the disciples and found them sleeping; and he said to Peter, "So, could you not stay awake with me one hour?
40原 26:41 Stay awake and pray that you may not come into the time of trial; the spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak."
40原 26:42 Again he went away for the second time and prayed, "My Father, if this cannot pass unless I drink it, your will be done."
40原 26:43 Again he came and found them sleeping, for their eyes were heavy.
40原 26:44 So leaving them again, he went away and prayed for the third time, saying the same words.
40原 26:45 Then he came to the disciples and said to them, "Are you still sleeping and taking your rest? See, the hour is at hand, and the Son of Man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
40原 26:46 Get up, let us be going. See, my betrayer is at hand."
40原 26:47 While he was still speaking, Judas, one of the twelve, arrived; with him was a large crowd with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and the elders of the people.
40原 26:48 Now the betrayer had given them a sign, saying, "The one I will kiss is the man; arrest him."
40原 26:49 At once he came up to Jesus and said, "Greetings, Rabbi!" and kissed him.
40原 26:50 Jesus said to him, "Friend, do what you are here to do." Then they came and laid hands on Jesus and arrested him.
40原 26:51 Suddenly, one of those with Jesus put his hand on his sword, drew it, and struck the slave of the high priest, cutting off his ear.
40原 26:52 Then Jesus said to him, "Put your sword back into its place; for all who take the sword will perish by the sword.
40原 26:53 Do you think that I cannot appeal to my Father, and he will at once send me more than twelve legions of angels?
40原 26:54 But how then would the scriptures be fulfilled, which say it must happen in this way?"
40原 26:55 At that hour Jesus said to the crowds, "Have you come out with swords and clubs to arrest me as though I were a bandit? Day after day I sat in the temple teaching, and you did not arrest me.
40原 26:56 But all this has taken place, so that the scriptures of the prophets may be fulfilled." Then all the disciples deserted him and fled.
40原 26:57 Those who had arrested Jesus took him to Caiaphas the high priest, in whose house the scribes and the elders had gathered.
40原 26:58 But Peter was following him at a distance, as far as the courtyard of the high priest; and going inside, he sat with the guards in order to see how this would end.
40原 26:59 Now the chief priests and the whole council were looking for false testimony against Jesus so that they might put him to death,
40原 26:60 but they found none, though many false witnesses came forward. At last two came forward
40原 26:61 and said, "This fellow said, 'I am able to destroy the temple of God and to build it in three days.'"
40原 26:62 The high priest stood up and said, "Have you no answer? What is it that they testify against you?"
40原 26:63 But Jesus was silent. Then the high priest said to him, "I put you under oath before the living God, tell us if you are the Messiah, the Son of God."
40原 26:64 Jesus said to him, "You have said so. But I tell you, From now on you will see the Son of Man seated at the right hand of Power and coming on the clouds of heaven."
40原 26:65 Then the high priest tore his clothes and said, "He has blasphemed! Why do we still need witnesses? You have now heard his blasphemy.
40原 26:66 What is your verdict?" They answered, "He deserves death."
40原 26:67 Then they spat in his face and struck him; and some slapped him,
40原 26:68 saying, "Prophesy to us, you Messiah! Who is it that struck you?"
40原 26:69 Now Peter was sitting outside in the courtyard. A servant-girl came to him and said, "You also were with Jesus the Galilean."
40原 26:70 But he denied it before all of them, saying, "I do not know what you are talking about."
40原 26:71 When he went out to the porch, another servant-girl saw him, and she said to the bystanders, "This man was with Jesus of Nazareth."
40原 26:72 Again he denied it with an oath, "I do not know the man."
40原 26:73 After a little while the bystanders came up and said to Peter, "Certainly you are also one of them, for your accent betrays you."
40原 26:74 Then he began to curse, and he swore an oath, "I do not know the man!" At that moment the cock crowed.
40原 26:75 Then Peter remembered what Jesus had said: "Before the cock crows, you will deny me three times." And he went out and wept bitterly.
40原 27:1 When morning came, all the chief priests and the elders of the people conferred together against Jesus in order to bring about his death.
40原 27:2 They bound him, led him away, and handed him over to Pilate the governor.
40原 27:3 When Judas, his betrayer, saw that Jesus was condemned, he repented and brought back the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and the elders.
40原 27:4 He said, "I have sinned by betraying innocent blood." But they said, "What is that to us? See to it yourself."
40原 27:5 Throwing down the pieces of silver in the temple, he departed; and he went and hanged himself.
40原 27:6 But the chief priests, taking the pieces of silver, said, "It is not lawful to put them into the treasury, since they are blood money."
40原 27:7 After conferring together, they used them to buy the potter's field as a place to bury foreigners.
40原 27:8 For this reason that field has been called the Field of Blood to this day.
40原 27:9 Then was fulfilled what had been spoken through the prophet Jeremiah, "And they took the thirty pieces of silver, the price of the one on whom a price had been set, on whom some of the people of Israel had set a price,
40原 27:10 and they gave them for the potter's field, as the Lord commanded me."
40原 27:11 Now Jesus stood before the governor; and the governor asked him, "Are you the King of the Jews?" Jesus said, "You say so."
40原 27:12 But when he was accused by the chief priests and elders, he did not answer.
40原 27:13 Then Pilate said to him, "Do you not hear how many accusations they make against you?"
40原 27:14 But he gave him no answer, not even to a single charge, so that the governor was greatly amazed.
40原 27:15 Now at the festival the governor was accustomed to release a prisoner for the crowd, anyone whom they wanted.
40原 27:16 At that time they had a notorious prisoner, called Jesus Barabbas.
40原 27:17 So after they had gathered, Pilate said to them, "Whom do you want me to release for you, Jesus Barabbas or Jesus who is called the Messiah?"
40原 27:18 For he realized that it was out of jealousy that they had handed him over.
40原 27:19 While he was sitting on the judgment seat, his wife sent word to him, "Have nothing to do with that innocent man, for today I have suffered a great deal because of a dream about him."
40原 27:20 Now the chief priests and the elders persuaded the crowds to ask for Barabbas and to have Jesus killed.
40原 27:21 The governor again said to them, "Which of the two do you want me to release for you?" And they said, "Barabbas."
40原 27:22 Pilate said to them, "Then what should I do with Jesus who is called the Messiah?" All of them said, "Let him be crucified!"
40原 27:23 Then he asked, "Why, what evil has he done?" But they shouted all the more, "Let him be crucified!"
40原 27:24 So when Pilate saw that he could do nothing, but rather that a riot was beginning, he took some water and washed his hands before the crowd, saying, "I am innocent of this man's blood; see to it yourselves."
40原 27:25 Then the people as a whole answered, "His blood be on us and on our children!"
40原 27:26 So he released Barabbas for them; and after flogging Jesus, he handed him over to be crucified.
40原 27:27 Then the soldiers of the governor took Jesus into the governor's headquarters, and they gathered the whole cohort around him.
40原 27:28 They stripped him and put a scarlet robe on him,
40原 27:29 and after twisting some thorns into a crown, they put it on his head. They put a reed in his right hand and knelt before him and mocked him, saying, "Hail, King of the Jews!"
40原 27:30 They spat on him, and took the reed and struck him on the head.
40原 27:31 After mocking him, they stripped him of the robe and put his own clothes on him. Then they led him away to crucify him.
40原 27:32 As they went out, they came upon a man from Cyrene named Simon; they compelled this man to carry his cross.
40原 27:33 And when they came to a place called Golgotha (which means Place of a Skull),
40原 27:34 they offered him wine to drink, mixed with gall; but when he tasted it, he would not drink it.
40原 27:35 And when they had crucified him, they divided his clothes among themselves by casting lots;
40原 27:36 then they sat down there and kept watch over him.
40原 27:37 Over his head they put the charge against him, which read, "This is Jesus, the King of the Jews."
40原 27:38 Then two bandits were crucified with him, one on his right and one on his left.
40原 27:39 Those who passed by derided him, shaking their heads
40原 27:40 and saying, "You who would destroy the temple and build it in three days, save yourself! If you are the Son of God, come down from the cross."
40原 27:41 In the same way the chief priests also, along with the scribes and elders, were mocking him, saying,
40原 27:42 "He saved others; he cannot save himself. He is the King of Israel; let him come down from the cross now, and we will believe in him.
40原 27:43 He trusts in God; let God deliver him now, if he wants to; for he said, 'I am God's Son.'"
40原 27:44 The bandits who were crucified with him also taunted him in the same way.
40原 27:45 From noon on, darkness came over the whole land until three in the afternoon.
40原 27:46 And about three o'clock Jesus cried with a loud voice, "Eli, Eli, lema sabachthani?" that is, "My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?"
40原 27:47 When some of the bystanders heard it, they said, "This man is calling for Elijah."
40原 27:48 At once one of them ran and got a sponge, filled it with sour wine, put it on a stick, and gave it to him to drink.
40原 27:49 But the others said, "Wait, let us see whether Elijah will come to save him."
40原 27:50 Then Jesus cried again with a loud voice and breathed his last.
40原 27:51 At that moment the curtain of the temple was torn in two, from top to bottom. The earth shook, and the rocks were split.
40原 27:52 The tombs also were opened, and many bodies of the saints who had fallen asleep were raised.
40原 27:53 After his resurrection they came out of the tombs and entered the holy city and appeared to many.
40原 27:54 Now when the centurion and those with him, who were keeping watch over Jesus, saw the earthquake and what took place, they were terrified and said, "Truly this man was God's Son!"
40原 27:55 Many women were also there, looking on from a distance; they had followed Jesus from Galilee and had provided for him.
40原 27:56 Among them were Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James and Joseph, and the mother of the sons of Zebedee.
40原 27:57 When it was evening, there came a rich man from Arimathea, named Joseph, who was also a disciple of Jesus.
40原 27:58 He went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus; then Pilate ordered it to be given to him.
40原 27:59 So Joseph took the body and wrapped it in a clean linen cloth
40原 27:60 and laid it in his own new tomb, which he had hewn in the rock. He then rolled a great stone to the door of the tomb and went away.
40原 27:61 Mary Magdalene and the other Mary were there, sitting opposite the tomb.
40原 27:62 The next day, that is, after the day of Preparation, the chief priests and the Pharisees gathered before Pilate
40原 27:63 and said, "Sir, we remember what that impostor said while he was still alive, 'After three days I will rise again.'
40原 27:64 Therefore command the tomb to be made secure until the third day; otherwise his disciples may go and steal him away, and tell the people, 'He has been raised from the dead,' and the last deception would be worse than the first."
40原 27:65 Pilate said to them, "You have a guard of soldiers; go, make it as secure as you can."
40原 27:66 So they went with the guard and made the tomb secure by sealing the stone.
40原 28:1 After the sabbath, as the first day of the week was dawning, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary went to see the tomb.
40原 28:2 And suddenly there was a great earthquake; for an angel of the Lord, descending from heaven, came and rolled back the stone and sat on it.
40原 28:3 His appearance was like lightning, and his clothing white as snow.
40原 28:4 For fear of him the guards shook and became like dead men.
40原 28:5 But the angel said to the women, "Do not be afraid; I know that you are looking for Jesus who was crucified.
40原 28:6 He is not here; for he has been raised, as he said. Come, see the place where he lay.
40原 28:7 Then go quickly and tell his disciples, 'He has been raised from the dead, and indeed he is going ahead of you to Galilee; there you will see him.' This is my message for you."
40原 28:8 So they left the tomb quickly with fear and great joy, and ran to tell his disciples.
40原 28:9 Suddenly Jesus met them and said, "Greetings!" And they came to him, took hold of his feet, and worshiped him.
40原 28:10 Then Jesus said to them, "Do not be afraid; go and tell my brothers to go to Galilee; there they will see me."
40原 28:11 While they were going, some of the guard went into the city and told the chief priests everything that had happened.
40原 28:12 After the priests had assembled with the elders, they devised a plan to give a large sum of money to the soldiers,
40原 28:13 telling them, "You must say, 'His disciples came by night and stole him away while we were asleep.'
40原 28:14 If this comes to the governor's ears, we will satisfy him and keep you out of trouble."
40原 28:15 So they took the money and did as they were directed. And this story is still told among the Jews to this day.
40原 28:16 Now the eleven disciples went to Galilee, to the mountain to which Jesus had directed them.
40原 28:17 When they saw him, they worshiped him; but some doubted.
40原 28:18 And Jesus came and said to them, "All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me.
40原 28:19 Go therefore and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit,
40原 28:20 and teaching them to obey everything that I have commanded you. And remember, I am with you always, to the end of the age."
