42勘 14:30 saying, 'This fellow began to build and was not able to finish.'
42勘 14:31 Or what king, going out to wage war against another king, will not sit down first and consider whether he is able with ten thousand to oppose the one who comes against him with twenty thousand?
42勘 14:32 If he cannot, then, while the other is still far away, he sends a delegation and asks for the terms of peace.
42勘 14:33 So therefore, none of you can become my disciple if you do not give up all your possessions.
42勘 14:34 "Salt is good; but if salt has lost its taste, how can its saltiness be restored?
42勘 14:35 It is fit neither for the soil nor for the manure pile; they throw it away. Let anyone with ears to hear listen!"
42勘 15:1 Now all the tax collectors and sinners were coming near to listen to him.
42勘 15:2 And the Pharisees and the scribes were grumbling and saying, "This fellow welcomes sinners and eats with them."
42勘 15:3 So he told them this parable:
42勘 15:4 "Which one of you, having a hundred sheep and losing one of them, does not leave the ninety-nine in the wilderness and go after the one that is lost until he finds it?
42勘 15:5 When he has found it, he lays it on his shoulders and rejoices.
42勘 15:6 And when he comes home, he calls together his friends and neighbors, saying to them, 'Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep that was lost.'
42勘 15:7 Just so, I tell you, there will be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who need no repentance.
42勘 15:8 "Or what woman having ten silver coins, if she loses one of them, does not light a lamp, sweep the house, and search carefully until she finds it?
42勘 15:9 When she has found it, she calls together her friends and neighbors, saying, 'Rejoice with me, for I have found the coin that I had lost.'
