42勘 15:13 A few days later the younger son gathered all he had and traveled to a distant country, and there he squandered his property in dissolute living.
42勘 15:14 When he had spent everything, a severe famine took place throughout that country, and he began to be in need.
42勘 15:15 So he went and hired himself out to one of the citizens of that country, who sent him to his fields to feed the pigs.
42勘 15:16 He would gladly have filled himself with the pods that the pigs were eating; and no one gave him anything.
42勘 15:17 But when he came to himself he said, 'How many of my father's hired hands have bread enough and to spare, but here I am dying of hunger!
42勘 15:18 I will get up and go to my father, and I will say to him, "Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you;
42勘 15:19 I am no longer worthy to be called your son; treat me like one of your hired hands."'
42勘 15:20 So he set off and went to his father. But while he was still far off, his father saw him and was filled with compassion; he ran and put his arms around him and kissed him.
42勘 15:21 Then the son said to him, 'Father, I have sinned against heaven and before you; I am no longer worthy to be called your son.'
42勘 15:22 But the father said to his slaves, 'Quickly, bring out a robe--the best one--and put it on him; put a ring on his finger and sandals on his feet.
42勘 15:23 And get the fatted calf and kill it, and let us eat and celebrate;
42勘 15:24 for this son of mine was dead and is alive again; he was lost and is found!' And they began to celebrate.
42勘 15:25 "Now his elder son was in the field; and when he came and approached the house, he heard music and dancing.
42勘 15:26 He called one of the slaves and asked what was going on.
42勘 15:27 He replied, 'Your brother has come, and your father has killed the fatted calf, because he has got him back safe and sound.'
42勘 15:28 Then he became angry and refused to go in. His father came out and began to plead with him.
42勘 15:29 But he answered his father, 'Listen! For all these years I have been working like a slave for you, and I have never disobeyed your command; yet you have never given me even a young goat so that I might celebrate with my friends.
42勘 15:30 But when this son of yours came back, who has devoured your property with prostitutes, you killed the fatted calf for him!'
42勘 15:31 Then the father said to him, 'Son, you are always with me, and all that is mine is yours.
42勘 15:32 But we had to celebrate and rejoice, because this brother of yours was dead and has come to life; he was lost and has been found.'"
42勘 16:1 Then Jesus said to the disciples, "There was a rich man who had a manager, and charges were brought to him that this man was squandering his property.
42勘 16:2 So he summoned him and said to him, 'What is this that I hear about you? Give me an accounting of your management, because you cannot be my manager any longer.'
42勘 16:3 Then the manager said to himself, 'What will I do, now that my master is taking the position away from me? I am not strong enough to dig, and I am ashamed to beg.
42勘 16:4 I have decided what to do so that, when I am dismissed as manager, people may welcome me into their homes.'
42勘 16:5 So, summoning his master's debtors one by one, he asked the first, 'How much do you owe my master?'
42勘 16:6 He answered, 'A hundred jugs of olive oil.' He said to him, 'Take your bill, sit down quickly, and make it fifty.'
42勘 16:7 Then he asked another, 'And how much do you owe?' He replied, 'A hundred containers of wheat.' He said to him, 'Take your bill and make it eighty.'
42勘 16:8 And his master commended the dishonest manager because he had acted shrewdly; for the children of this age are more shrewd in dealing with their own generation than are the children of light.
42勘 16:9 And I tell you, make friends for yourselves by means of dishonest wealth so that when it is gone, they may welcome you into the eternal homes.
42勘 16:10 "Whoever is faithful in a very little is faithful also in much; and whoever is dishonest in a very little is dishonest also in much.
42勘 16:11 If then you have not been faithful with the dishonest wealth, who will entrust to you the true riches?
42勘 16:12 And if you have not been faithful with what belongs to another, who will give you what is your own?
42勘 16:13 No slave can serve two masters; for a slave will either hate the one and love the other, or be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve God and wealth."
42勘 16:14 The Pharisees, who were lovers of money, heard all this, and they ridiculed him.
42勘 16:15 So he said to them, "You are those who justify yourselves in the sight of others; but God knows your hearts; for what is prized by human beings is an abomination in the sight of God.
42勘 16:16 "The law and the prophets were in effect until John came; since then the good news of the kingdom of God is proclaimed, and everyone tries to enter it by force.
42勘 16:17 But it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away, than for one stroke of a letter in the law to be dropped.
42勘 16:18 "Anyone who divorces his wife and marries another commits adultery, and whoever marries a woman divorced from her husband commits adultery.
42勘 16:19 "There was a rich man who was dressed in purple and fine linen and who feasted sumptuously every day.
42勘 16:20 And at his gate lay a poor man named Lazarus, covered with sores,
42勘 16:21 who longed to satisfy his hunger with what fell from the rich man's table; even the dogs would come and lick his sores.
42勘 16:22 The poor man died and was carried away by the angels to be with Abraham. The rich man also died and was buried.
42勘 16:23 In Hades, where he was being tormented, he looked up and saw Abraham far away with Lazarus by his side.
42勘 16:24 He called out, 'Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus to dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my tongue; for I am in agony in these flames.'
42勘 16:25 But Abraham said, 'Child, remember that during your lifetime you received your good things, and Lazarus in like manner evil things; but now he is comforted here, and you are in agony.
42勘 16:26 Besides all this, between you and us a great chasm has been fixed, so that those who might want to pass from here to you cannot do so, and no one can cross from there to us.'
42勘 16:27 He said, 'Then, father, I beg you to send him to my father's house--
42勘 16:28 for I have five brothers--that he may warn them, so that they will not also come into this place of torment.'
42勘 16:29 Abraham replied, 'They have Moses and the prophets; they should listen to them.'
42勘 16:30 He said, 'No, father Abraham; but if someone goes to them from the dead, they will repent.'
42勘 16:31 He said to him, 'If they do not listen to Moses and the prophets, neither will they be convinced even if someone rises from the dead.'"
42勘 17:1 Jesus said to his disciples, "Occasions for stumbling are bound to come, but woe to anyone by whom they come!
