42勘 18:26 Those who heard it said, "Then who can be saved?"
42勘 18:27 He replied, "What is impossible for mortals is possible for God."
42勘 18:28 Then Peter said, "Look, we have left our homes and followed you."
42勘 18:29 And he said to them, "Truly I tell you, there is no one who has left house or wife or brothers or parents or children, for the sake of the kingdom of God,
42勘 18:30 who will not get back very much more in this age, and in the age to come eternal life."
42勘 18:31 Then he took the twelve aside and said to them, "See, we are going up to Jerusalem, and everything that is written about the Son of Man by the prophets will be accomplished.
42勘 18:32 For he will be handed over to the Gentiles; and he will be mocked and insulted and spat upon.
42勘 18:33 After they have flogged him, they will kill him, and on the third day he will rise again."
