42勘 18:35 As he approached Jericho, a blind man was sitting by the roadside begging.
42勘 18:36 When he heard a crowd going by, he asked what was happening.
42勘 18:37 They told him, "Jesus of Nazareth is passing by."
42勘 18:38 Then he shouted, "Jesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!"
42勘 18:39 Those who were in front sternly ordered him to be quiet; but he shouted even more loudly, "Son of David, have mercy on me!"
42勘 18:40 Jesus stood still and ordered the man to be brought to him; and when he came near, he asked him,
42勘 18:41 "What do you want me to do for you?" He said, "Lord, let me see again."
42勘 18:42 Jesus said to him, "Receive your sight; your faith has saved you."
42勘 18:43 Immediately he regained his sight and followed him, glorifying God; and all the people, when they saw it, praised God.
42勘 19:1 He entered Jericho and was passing through it.
42勘 19:2 A man was there named Zacchaeus; he was a chief tax collector and was rich.
42勘 19:3 He was trying to see who Jesus was, but on account of the crowd he could not, because he was short in stature.
42勘 19:4 So he ran ahead and climbed a sycamore tree to see him, because he was going to pass that way.
42勘 19:5 When Jesus came to the place, he looked up and said to him, "Zacchaeus, hurry and come down; for I must stay at your house today."
42勘 19:6 So he hurried down and was happy to welcome him.
42勘 19:7 All who saw it began to grumble and said, "He has gone to be the guest of one who is a sinner."
42勘 19:8 Zacchaeus stood there and said to the Lord, "Look, half of my possessions, Lord, I will give to the poor; and if I have defrauded anyone of anything, I will pay back four times as much."
42勘 19:9 Then Jesus said to him, "Today salvation has come to this house, because he too is a son of Abraham.
42勘 19:10 For the Son of Man came to seek out and to save the lost."
42勘 19:11 As they were listening to this, he went on to tell a parable, because he was near Jerusalem, and because they supposed that the kingdom of God was to appear immediately.
42勘 19:12 So he said, "A nobleman went to a distant country to get royal power for himself and then return.
42勘 19:13 He summoned ten of his slaves, and gave them ten pounds, and said to them, 'Do business with these until I come back.'
42勘 19:14 But the citizens of his country hated him and sent a delegation after him, saying, 'We do not want this man to rule over us.'
42勘 19:15 When he returned, having received royal power, he ordered these slaves, to whom he had given the money, to be summoned so that he might find out what they had gained by trading.
42勘 19:16 The first came forward and said, 'Lord, your pound has made ten more pounds.'
42勘 19:17 He said to him, 'Well done, good slave! Because you have been trustworthy in a very small thing, take charge of ten cities.'
42勘 19:18 Then the second came, saying, 'Lord, your pound has made five pounds.'
42勘 19:19 He said to him, 'And you, rule over five cities.'
42勘 19:20 Then the other came, saying, 'Lord, here is your pound. I wrapped it up in a piece of cloth,
42勘 19:21 for I was afraid of you, because you are a harsh man; you take what you did not deposit, and reap what you did not sow.'
42勘 19:22 He said to him, 'I will judge you by your own words, you wicked slave! You knew, did you, that I was a harsh man, taking what I did not deposit and reaping what I did not sow?
42勘 19:23 Why then did you not put my money into the bank? Then when I returned, I could have collected it with interest.'
42勘 19:24 He said to the bystanders, 'Take the pound from him and give it to the one who has ten pounds.'
42勘 19:25 (And they said to him, 'Lord, he has ten pounds!')
42勘 19:26 'I tell you, to all those who have, more will be given; but from those who have nothing, even what they have will be taken away.
42勘 19:27 But as for these enemies of mine who did not want me to be king over them--bring them here and slaughter them in my presence.'"
42勘 19:28 After he had said this, he went on ahead, going up to Jerusalem.
42勘 19:29 When he had come near Bethphage and Bethany, at the place called the Mount of Olives, he sent two of the disciples,
42勘 19:30 saying, "Go into the village ahead of you, and as you enter it you will find tied there a colt that has never been ridden. Untie it and bring it here.
42勘 19:31 If anyone asks you, 'Why are you untying it?' just say this, 'The Lord needs it.'"
42勘 19:32 So those who were sent departed and found it as he had told them.
42勘 19:33 As they were untying the colt, its owners asked them, "Why are you untying the colt?"
42勘 19:34 They said, "The Lord needs it."
42勘 19:35 Then they brought it to Jesus; and after throwing their cloaks on the colt, they set Jesus on it.
42勘 19:36 As he rode along, people kept spreading their cloaks on the road.
42勘 19:37 As he was now approaching the path down from the Mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to praise God joyfully with a loud voice for all the deeds of power that they had seen,
42勘 19:38 saying, "Blessed is the king who comes in the name of the Lord! Peace in heaven, and glory in the highest heaven!"
42勘 19:39 Some of the Pharisees in the crowd said to him, "Teacher, order your disciples to stop."
42勘 19:40 He answered, "I tell you, if these were silent, the stones would shout out."
42勘 19:41 As he came near and saw the city, he wept over it,
42勘 19:42 saying, "If you, even you, had only recognized on this day the things that make for peace! But now they are hidden from your eyes.
42勘 19:43 Indeed, the days will come upon you, when your enemies will set up ramparts around you and surround you, and hem you in on every side.
42勘 19:44 They will crush you to the ground, you and your children within you, and they will not leave within you one stone upon another; because you did not recognize the time of your visitation from God."
42勘 19:45 Then he entered the temple and began to drive out those who were selling things there;
42勘 19:46 and he said, "It is written, 'My house shall be a house of prayer'; but you have made it a den of robbers."
42勘 19:47 Every day he was teaching in the temple. The chief priests, the scribes, and the leaders of the people kept looking for a way to kill him;
42勘 19:48 but they did not find anything they could do, for all the people were spellbound by what they heard.
42勘 20:1 One day, as he was teaching the people in the temple and telling the good news, the chief priests and the scribes came with the elders
42勘 20:2 and said to him, "Tell us, by what authority are you doing these things? Who is it who gave you this authority?"
42勘 20:3 He answered them, "I will also ask you a question, and you tell me:
42勘 20:4 Did the baptism of John come from heaven, or was it of human origin?"
42勘 20:5 They discussed it with one another, saying, "If we say, 'From heaven,' he will say, 'Why did you not believe him?'
42勘 20:6 But if we say, 'Of human origin,' all the people will stone us; for they are convinced that John was a prophet."
42勘 20:7 So they answered that they did not know where it came from.
42勘 20:8 Then Jesus said to them, "Neither will I tell you by what authority I am doing these things."
42勘 20:9 He began to tell the people this parable: "A man planted a vineyard, and leased it to tenants, and went to another country for a long time.
42勘 20:10 When the season came, he sent a slave to the tenants in order that they might give him his share of the produce of the vineyard; but the tenants beat him and sent him away empty-handed.
42勘 20:11 Next he sent another slave; that one also they beat and insulted and sent away empty-handed.
42勘 20:12 And he sent still a third; this one also they wounded and threw out.
42勘 20:13 Then the owner of the vineyard said, 'What shall I do? I will send my beloved son; perhaps they will respect him.'
42勘 20:14 But when the tenants saw him, they discussed it among themselves and said, 'This is the heir; let us kill him so that the inheritance may be ours.'
42勘 20:15 So they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him. What then will the owner of the vineyard do to them?
42勘 20:16 He will come and destroy those tenants and give the vineyard to others." When they heard this, they said, "Heaven forbid!"
42勘 20:17 But he looked at them and said, "What then does this text mean: 'The stone that the builders rejected has become the cornerstone'?
42勘 20:18 Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces; and it will crush anyone on whom it falls."
42勘 20:19 When the scribes and chief priests realized that he had told this parable against them, they wanted to lay hands on him at that very hour, but they feared the people.
42勘 20:20 So they watched him and sent spies who pretended to be honest, in order to trap him by what he said, so as to hand him over to the jurisdiction and authority of the governor.
42勘 20:21 So they asked him, "Teacher, we know that you are right in what you say and teach, and you show deference to no one, but teach the way of God in accordance with truth.
42勘 20:22 Is it lawful for us to pay taxes to the emperor, or not?"
42勘 20:23 But he perceived their craftiness and said to them,
42勘 20:24 "Show me a denarius. Whose head and whose title does it bear?" They said, "The emperor's."
42勘 20:25 He said to them, "Then give to the emperor the things that are the emperor's, and to God the things that are God's."
42勘 20:26 And they were not able in the presence of the people to trap him by what he said; and being amazed by his answer, they became silent.
42勘 20:27 Some Sadducees, those who say there is no resurrection, came to him
42勘 20:28 and asked him a question, "Teacher, Moses wrote for us that if a man's brother dies, leaving a wife but no children, the man shall marry the widow and raise up children for his brother.
42勘 20:29 Now there were seven brothers; the first married, and died childless;
42勘 20:30 then the second
42勘 20:31 and the third married her, and so in the same way all seven died childless.
42勘 20:32 Finally the woman also died.
42勘 20:33 In the resurrection, therefore, whose wife will the woman be? For the seven had married her."
42勘 20:34 Jesus said to them, "Those who belong to this age marry and are given in marriage;
42勘 20:35 but those who are considered worthy of a place in that age and in the resurrection from the dead neither marry nor are given in marriage.
42勘 20:36 Indeed they cannot die anymore, because they are like angels and are children of God, being children of the resurrection.
42勘 20:37 And the fact that the dead are raised Moses himself showed, in the story about the bush, where he speaks of the Lord as the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.
42勘 20:38 Now he is God not of the dead, but of the living; for to him all of them are alive."
42勘 20:39 Then some of the scribes answered, "Teacher, you have spoken well."
42勘 20:40 For they no longer dared to ask him another question.
42勘 20:41 Then he said to them, "How can they say that the Messiah is David's son?
42勘 20:42 For David himself says in the book of Psalms, 'The Lord said to my Lord, "Sit at my right hand,
42勘 20:43 until I make your enemies your footstool."
42勘 20:44 David thus calls him Lord; so how can he be his son?"
42勘 20:45 In the hearing of all the people he said to the disciples,
42勘 20:46 "Beware of the scribes, who like to walk around in long robes, and love to be greeted with respect in the marketplaces, and to have the best seats in the synagogues and places of honor at banquets.
42勘 20:47 They devour widows' houses and for the sake of appearance say long prayers. They will receive the greater condemnation."
42勘 21:1 He looked up and saw rich people putting their gifts into the treasury;
42勘 21:2 he also saw a poor widow put in two small copper coins.
42勘 21:3 He said, "Truly I tell you, this poor widow has put in more than all of them;
42勘 21:4 for all of them have contributed out of their abundance, but she out of her poverty has put in all she had to live on."
42勘 21:5 When some were speaking about the temple, how it was adorned with beautiful stones and gifts dedicated to God, he said,
42勘 21:6 "As for these things that you see, the days will come when not one stone will be left upon another; all will be thrown down."
42勘 21:7 They asked him, "Teacher, when will this be, and what will be the sign that this is about to take place?"
42勘 21:8 And he said, "Beware that you are not led astray; for many will come in my name and say, 'I am he!' and, 'The time is near!' Do not go after them.
42勘 21:9 "When you hear of wars and insurrections, do not be terrified; for these things must take place first, but the end will not follow immediately."
42勘 21:10 Then he said to them, "Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom;
42勘 21:11 there will be great earthquakes, and in various places famines and plagues; and there will be dreadful portents and great signs from heaven.
42勘 21:12 "But before all this occurs, they will arrest you and persecute you; they will hand you over to synagogues and prisons, and you will be brought before kings and governors because of my name.
42勘 21:13 This will give you an opportunity to testify.
42勘 21:14 So make up your minds not to prepare your defense in advance;
42勘 21:15 for I will give you words and a wisdom that none of your opponents will be able to withstand or contradict.
42勘 21:16 You will be betrayed even by parents and brothers, by relatives and friends; and they will put some of you to death.
42勘 21:17 You will be hated by all because of my name.
42勘 21:18 But not a hair of your head will perish.
42勘 21:19 By your endurance you will gain your souls.
42勘 21:20 "When you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then know that its desolation has come near.
42勘 21:21 Then those in Judea must flee to the mountains, and those inside the city must leave it, and those out in the country must not enter it;
42勘 21:22 for these are days of vengeance, as a fulfillment of all that is written.
42勘 21:23 Woe to those who are pregnant and to those who are nursing infants in those days! For there will be great distress on the earth and wrath against this people;
42勘 21:24 they will fall by the edge of the sword and be taken away as captives among all nations; and Jerusalem will be trampled on by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled.
42勘 21:25 "There will be signs in the sun, the moon, and the stars, and on the earth distress among nations confused by the roaring of the sea and the waves.
42勘 21:26 People will faint from fear and foreboding of what is coming upon the world, for the powers of the heavens will be shaken.
42勘 21:27 Then they will see 'the Son of Man coming in a cloud' with power and great glory.
42勘 21:28 Now when these things begin to take place, stand up and raise your heads, because your redemption is drawing near."
42勘 21:29 Then he told them a parable: "Look at the fig tree and all the trees;
42勘 21:30 as soon as they sprout leaves you can see for yourselves and know that summer is already near.
42勘 21:31 So also, when you see these things taking place, you know that the kingdom of God is near.
42勘 21:32 Truly I tell you, this generation will not pass away until all things have taken place.
42勘 21:33 Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.
42勘 21:34 "Be on guard so that your hearts are not weighed down with dissipation and drunkenness and the worries of this life, and that day catch you unexpectedly,
42勘 21:35 like a trap. For it will come upon all who live on the face of the whole earth.
42勘 21:36 Be alert at all times, praying that you may have the strength to escape all these things that will take place, and to stand before the Son of Man."
42勘 21:37 Every day he was teaching in the temple, and at night he would go out and spend the night on the Mount of Olives, as it was called.
42勘 21:38 And all the people would get up early in the morning to listen to him in the temple.
42勘 22:1 Now the festival of Unleavened Bread, which is called the Passover, was near.
42勘 22:2 The chief priests and the scribes were looking for a way to put Jesus to death, for they were afraid of the people.
42勘 22:3 Then Satan entered into Judas called Iscariot, who was one of the twelve;
42勘 22:4 he went away and conferred with the chief priests and officers of the temple police about how he might betray him to them.
42勘 22:5 They were greatly pleased and agreed to give him money.
42勘 22:6 So he consented and began to look for an opportunity to betray him to them when no crowd was present.
42勘 22:7 Then came the day of Unleavened Bread, on which the Passover lamb had to be sacrificed.
42勘 22:8 So Jesus sent Peter and John, saying, "Go and prepare the Passover meal for us that we may eat it."
42勘 22:9 They asked him, "Where do you want us to make preparations for it?"
42勘 22:10 "Listen," he said to them, "when you have entered the city, a man carrying a jar of water will meet you; follow him into the house he enters
42勘 22:11 and say to the owner of the house, 'The teacher asks you, "Where is the guest room, where I may eat the Passover with my disciples?"'
42勘 22:12 He will show you a large room upstairs, already furnished. Make preparations for us there."
42勘 22:13 So they went and found everything as he had told them; and they prepared the Passover meal.
42勘 22:14 When the hour came, he took his place at the table, and the apostles with him.
42勘 22:15 He said to them, "I have eagerly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer;
42勘 22:16 for I tell you, I will not eat it until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God."
42勘 22:17 Then he took a cup, and after giving thanks he said, "Take this and divide it among yourselves;
42勘 22:18 for I tell you that from now on I will not drink of the fruit of the vine until the kingdom of God comes."
42勘 22:19 Then he took a loaf of bread, and when he had given thanks, he broke it and gave it to them, saying, "This is my body, which is given for you. Do this in remembrance of me."
42勘 22:20 And he did the same with the cup after supper, saying, "This cup that is poured out for you is the new covenant in my blood.
42勘 22:21 But see, the one who betrays me is with me, and his hand is on the table.
42勘 22:22 For the Son of Man is going as it has been determined, but woe to that one by whom he is betrayed!"
42勘 22:23 Then they began to ask one another, which one of them it could be who would do this.
42勘 22:24 A dispute also arose among them as to which one of them was to be regarded as the greatest.
42勘 22:25 But he said to them, "The kings of the Gentiles lord it over them; and those in authority over them are called benefactors.
42勘 22:26 But not so with you; rather the greatest among you must become like the youngest, and the leader like one who serves.
42勘 22:27 For who is greater, the one who is at the table or the one who serves? Is it not the one at the table? But I am among you as one who serves.
42勘 22:28 "You are those who have stood by me in my trials;
42勘 22:29 and I confer on you, just as my Father has conferred on me, a kingdom,
42勘 22:30 so that you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and you will sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
42勘 22:31 "Simon, Simon, listen! Satan has demanded to sift all of you like wheat,
42勘 22:32 but I have prayed for you that your own faith may not fail; and you, when once you have turned back, strengthen your brothers."
42勘 22:33 And he said to him, "Lord, I am ready to go with you to prison and to death!"
42勘 22:34 Jesus said, "I tell you, Peter, the cock will not crow this day, until you have denied three times that you know me."
42勘 22:35 He said to them, "When I sent you out without a purse, bag, or sandals, did you lack anything?" They said, "No, not a thing."
42勘 22:36 He said to them, "But now, the one who has a purse must take it, and likewise a bag. And the one who has no sword must sell his cloak and buy one.
42勘 22:37 For I tell you, this scripture must be fulfilled in me, 'And he was counted among the lawless'; and indeed what is written about me is being fulfilled."
42勘 22:38 They said, "Lord, look, here are two swords." He replied, "It is enough."
42勘 22:39 He came out and went, as was his custom, to the Mount of Olives; and the disciples followed him.
42勘 22:40 When he reached the place, he said to them, "Pray that you may not come into the time of trial."
42勘 22:41 Then he withdrew from them about a stone's throw, knelt down, and prayed,
42勘 22:42 "Father, if you are willing, remove this cup from me; yet, not my will but yours be done."
42勘 22:43 Then an angel from heaven appeared to him and gave him strength.
42勘 22:44 In his anguish he prayed more earnestly, and his sweat became like great drops of blood falling down on the ground.
42勘 22:45 When he got up from prayer, he came to the disciples and found them sleeping because of grief,
42勘 22:46 and he said to them, "Why are you sleeping? Get up and pray that you may not come into the time of trial."
42勘 22:47 While he was still speaking, suddenly a crowd came, and the one called Judas, one of the twelve, was leading them. He approached Jesus to kiss him;
42勘 22:48 but Jesus said to him, "Judas, is it with a kiss that you are betraying the Son of Man?"
42勘 22:49 When those who were around him saw what was coming, they asked, "Lord, should we strike with the sword?"
42勘 22:50 Then one of them struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his right ear.
42勘 22:51 But Jesus said, "No more of this!" And he touched his ear and healed him.
42勘 22:52 Then Jesus said to the chief priests, the officers of the temple police, and the elders who had come for him, "Have you come out with swords and clubs as if I were a bandit?
42勘 22:53 When I was with you day after day in the temple, you did not lay hands on me. But this is your hour, and the power of darkness!"
42勘 22:54 Then they seized him and led him away, bringing him into the high priest's house. But Peter was following at a distance.
42勘 22:55 When they had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard and sat down together, Peter sat among them.
42勘 22:56 Then a servant-girl, seeing him in the firelight, stared at him and said, "This man also was with him."
42勘 22:57 But he denied it, saying, "Woman, I do not know him."
42勘 22:58 A little later someone else, on seeing him, said, "You also are one of them." But Peter said, "Man, I am not!"
42勘 22:59 Then about an hour later still another kept insisting, "Surely this man also was with him; for he is a Galilean."
42勘 22:60 But Peter said, "Man, I do not know what you are talking about!" At that moment, while he was still speaking, the cock crowed.
42勘 22:61 The Lord turned and looked at Peter. Then Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how he had said to him, "Before the cock crows today, you will deny me three times."
42勘 22:62 And he went out and wept bitterly.
42勘 22:63 Now the men who were holding Jesus began to mock him and beat him;
42勘 22:64 they also blindfolded him and kept asking him, "Prophesy! Who is it that struck you?"
42勘 22:65 They kept heaping many other insults on him.
42勘 22:66 When day came, the assembly of the elders of the people, both chief priests and scribes, gathered together, and they brought him to their council.
42勘 22:67 They said, "If you are the Messiah, tell us." He replied, "If I tell you, you will not believe;
42勘 22:68 and if I question you, you will not answer.
42勘 22:69 But from now on the Son of Man will be seated at the right hand of the power of God."
42勘 22:70 All of them asked, "Are you, then, the Son of God?" He said to them, "You say that I am."
42勘 22:71 Then they said, "What further testimony do we need? We have heard it ourselves from his own lips!"
42勘 23:1 Then the assembly rose as a body and brought Jesus before Pilate.
42勘 23:2 They began to accuse him, saying, "We found this man perverting our nation, forbidding us to pay taxes to the emperor, and saying that he himself is the Messiah, a king."
42勘 23:3 Then Pilate asked him, "Are you the king of the Jews?" He answered, "You say so."
42勘 23:4 Then Pilate said to the chief priests and the crowds, "I find no basis for an accusation against this man."
42勘 23:5 But they were insistent and said, "He stirs up the people by teaching throughout all Judea, from Galilee where he began even to this place."
42勘 23:6 When Pilate heard this, he asked whether the man was a Galilean.
42勘 23:7 And when he learned that he was under Herod's jurisdiction, he sent him off to Herod, who was himself in Jerusalem at that time.
42勘 23:8 When Herod saw Jesus, he was very glad, for he had been wanting to see him for a long time, because he had heard about him and was hoping to see him perform some sign.
42勘 23:9 He questioned him at some length, but Jesus gave him no answer.
42勘 23:10 The chief priests and the scribes stood by, vehemently accusing him.
42勘 23:11 Even Herod with his soldiers treated him with contempt and mocked him; then he put an elegant robe on him, and sent him back to Pilate.
42勘 23:12 That same day Herod and Pilate became friends with each other; before this they had been enemies.
42勘 23:13 Pilate then called together the chief priests, the leaders, and the people,
42勘 23:14 and said to them, "You brought me this man as one who was perverting the people; and here I have examined him in your presence and have not found this man guilty of any of your charges against him.
42勘 23:15 Neither has Herod, for he sent him back to us. Indeed, he has done nothing to deserve death.
42勘 23:16 I will therefore have him flogged and release him."
42勘 23:17 Now he was obliged to release someone for them at the festival.(貝須)
42勘 23:18 Then they all shouted out together, "Away with this fellow! Release Barabbas for us!"
42勘 23:19 (This was a man who had been put in prison for an insurrection that had taken place in the city, and for murder.)
42勘 23:20 Pilate, wanting to release Jesus, addressed them again;
42勘 23:21 but they kept shouting, "Crucify, crucify him!"
42勘 23:22 A third time he said to them, "Why, what evil has he done? I have found in him no ground for the sentence of death; I will therefore have him flogged and then release him."
42勘 23:23 But they kept urgently demanding with loud shouts that he should be crucified; and their voices prevailed.
42勘 23:24 So Pilate gave his verdict that their demand should be granted.
42勘 23:25 He released the man they asked for, the one who had been put in prison for insurrection and murder, and he handed Jesus over as they wished.
42勘 23:26 As they led him away, they seized a man, Simon of Cyrene, who was coming from the country, and they laid the cross on him, and made him carry it behind Jesus.
42勘 23:27 A great number of the people followed him, and among them were women who were beating their breasts and wailing for him.
42勘 23:28 But Jesus turned to them and said, "Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.
42勘 23:29 For the days are surely coming when they will say, 'Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bore, and the breasts that never nursed.'
42勘 23:30 Then they will begin to say to the mountains, 'Fall on us'; and to the hills, 'Cover us.'
42勘 23:31 For if they do this when the wood is green, what will happen when it is dry?"
42勘 23:32 Two others also, who were criminals, were led away to be put to death with him.
42勘 23:33 When they came to the place that is called The Skull, they crucified Jesus there with the criminals, one on his right and one on his left.
42勘 23:34 Then Jesus said, "Father, forgive them; for they do not know what they are doing." And they cast lots to divide his clothing.
42勘 23:35 And the people stood by, watching; but the leaders scoffed at him, saying, "He saved others; let him save himself if he is the Messiah of God, his chosen one!"
42勘 23:36 The soldiers also mocked him, coming up and offering him sour wine,
42勘 23:37 and saying, "If you are the King of the Jews, save yourself!"
42勘 23:38 There was also an inscription over him, "This is the King of the Jews."
42勘 23:39 One of the criminals who were hanged there kept deriding him and saying, "Are you not the Messiah? Save yourself and us!"
42勘 23:40 But the other rebuked him, saying, "Do you not fear God, since you are under the same sentence of condemnation?
42勘 23:41 And we indeed have been condemned justly, for we are getting what we deserve for our deeds, but this man has done nothing wrong."
42勘 23:42 Then he said, "Jesus, remember me when you come into your kingdom."
42勘 23:43 He replied, "Truly I tell you, today you will be with me in Paradise."
42勘 23:44 It was now about noon, and darkness came over the whole land until three in the afternoon,
42勘 23:45 while the sun's light failed; and the curtain of the temple was torn in two.
42勘 23:46 Then Jesus, crying with a loud voice, said, "Father, into your hands I commend my spirit." Having said this, he breathed his last.
42勘 23:47 When the centurion saw what had taken place, he praised God and said, "Certainly this man was innocent."
42勘 23:48 And when all the crowds who had gathered there for this spectacle saw what had taken place, they returned home, beating their breasts.
42勘 23:49 But all his acquaintances, including the women who had followed him from Galilee, stood at a distance, watching these things.
42勘 23:50 Now there was a good and righteous man named Joseph, who, though a member of the council,
42勘 23:51 had not agreed to their plan and action. He came from the Jewish town of Arimathea, and he was waiting expectantly for the kingdom of God.
42勘 23:52 This man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.
42勘 23:53 Then he took it down, wrapped it in a linen cloth, and laid it in a rock-hewn tomb where no one had ever been laid.
42勘 23:54 It was the day of Preparation, and the sabbath was beginning.
42勘 23:55 The women who had come with him from Galilee followed, and they saw the tomb and how his body was laid.
42勘 23:56 Then they returned, and prepared spices and ointments. On the sabbath they rested according to the commandment.
42勘 24:1 But on the first day of the week, at early dawn, they came to the tomb, taking the spices that they had prepared.
42勘 24:2 They found the stone rolled away from the tomb,
42勘 24:3 but when they went in, they did not find the body.
42勘 24:4 While they were perplexed about this, suddenly two men in dazzling clothes stood beside them.
42勘 24:5 The women were terrified and bowed their faces to the ground, but the men said to them, "Why do you look for the living among the dead? He is not here, but has risen.
42勘 24:6 Remember how he told you, while he was still in Galilee,
42勘 24:7 that the Son of Man must be handed over to sinners, and be crucified, and on the third day rise again."
42勘 24:8 Then they remembered his words,
42勘 24:9 and returning from the tomb, they told all this to the eleven and to all the rest.
42勘 24:10 Now it was Mary Magdalene, Joanna, Mary the mother of James, and the other women with them who told this to the apostles.
42勘 24:11 But these words seemed to them an idle tale, and they did not believe them.
42勘 24:12 But Peter got up and ran to the tomb; stooping and looking in, he saw the linen cloths by themselves; then he went home, amazed at what had happened.
42勘 24:13 Now on that same day two of them were going to a village called Emmaus, about seven miles from Jerusalem,
42勘 24:14 and talking with each other about all these things that had happened.
42勘 24:15 While they were talking and discussing, Jesus himself came near and went with them,
42勘 24:16 but their eyes were kept from recognizing him.
42勘 24:17 And he said to them, "What are you discussing with each other while you walk along?" They stood still, looking sad.
42勘 24:18 Then one of them, whose name was Cleopas, answered him, "Are you the only stranger in Jerusalem who does not know the things that have taken place there in these days?"
42勘 24:19 He asked them, "What things?" They replied, "The things about Jesus of Nazareth, who was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people,
42勘 24:20 and how our chief priests and leaders handed him over to be condemned to death and crucified him.
42勘 24:21 But we had hoped that he was the one to redeem Israel. Yes, and besides all this, it is now the third day since these things took place.
42勘 24:22 Moreover, some women of our group astounded us. They were at the tomb early this morning,
42勘 24:23 and when they did not find his body there, they came back and told us that they had indeed seen a vision of angels who said that he was alive.
42勘 24:24 Some of those who were with us went to the tomb and found it just as the women had said; but they did not see him."
42勘 24:25 Then he said to them, "Oh, how foolish you are, and how slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have declared!
42勘 24:26 Was it not necessary that the Messiah should suffer these things and then enter into his glory?"
42勘 24:27 Then beginning with Moses and all the prophets, he interpreted to them the things about himself in all the scriptures.
