43推 1:13 who were born, not of blood or of the will of the flesh or of the will of man, but of God.
43推 1:14 And the Word became flesh and lived among us, and we have seen his glory, the glory as of a father's only son, full of grace and truth.
43推 1:15 (John testified to him and cried out, "This was he of whom I said, 'He who comes after me ranks ahead of me because he was before me.'")
43推 1:16 From his fullness we have all received, grace upon grace.
43推 1:17 The law indeed was given through Moses; grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.
43推 1:18 No one has ever seen God. It is God the only Son, who is close to the Father's heart, who has made him known.
43推 1:19 This is the testimony given by John when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, "Who are you?"
43推 1:20 He confessed and did not deny it, but confessed, "I am not the Messiah."
43推 1:21 And they asked him, "What then? Are you Elijah?" He said, "I am not." "Are you the prophet?" He answered, "No."
43推 1:22 Then they said to him, "Who are you? Let us have an answer for those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?"
43推 1:23 He said, "I am the voice of one crying out in the wilderness, 'Make straight the way of the Lord,'" as the prophet Isaiah said.
43推 1:24 Now they had been sent from the Pharisees.
43推 1:25 They asked him, "Why then are you baptizing if you are neither the Messiah, nor Elijah, nor the prophet?"
43推 1:26 John answered them, "I baptize with water. Among you stands one whom you do not know,
