43推 6:3 Jesus went up the mountain and sat down there with his disciples.
43推 6:4 Now the Passover, the festival of the Jews, was near.
43推 6:5 When he looked up and saw a large crowd coming toward him, Jesus said to Philip, "Where are we to buy bread for these people to eat?"
43推 6:6 He said this to test him, for he himself knew what he was going to do.
