43推 6:12 When they were satisfied, he told his disciples, "Gather up the fragments left over, so that nothing may be lost."
43推 6:13 So they gathered them up, and from the fragments of the five barley loaves, left by those who had eaten, they filled twelve baskets.
43推 6:14 When the people saw the sign that he had done, they began to say, "This is indeed the prophet who is to come into the world."
43推 6:15 When Jesus realized that they were about to come and take him by force to make him king, he withdrew again to the mountain by himself.
43推 6:16 When evening came, his disciples went down to the sea,
43推 6:17 got into a boat, and started across the sea to Capernaum. It was now dark, and Jesus had not yet come to them.
43推 6:18 The sea became rough because a strong wind was blowing.
43推 6:19 When they had rowed about three or four miles, they saw Jesus walking on the sea and coming near the boat, and they were terrified.
43推 6:20 But he said to them, "It is I; do not be afraid."
43推 6:21 Then they wanted to take him into the boat, and immediately the boat reached the land toward which they were going.
43推 6:22 The next day the crowd that had stayed on the other side of the sea saw that there had been only one boat there. They also saw that Jesus had not got into the boat with his disciples, but that his disciples had gone away alone.
43推 6:23 Then some boats from Tiberias came near the place where they had eaten the bread after the Lord had given thanks.
43推 6:24 So when the crowd saw that neither Jesus nor his disciples were there, they themselves got into the boats and went to Capernaum looking for Jesus.
43推 6:25 When they found him on the other side of the sea, they said to him, "Rabbi, when did you come here?"
43推 6:26 Jesus answered them, "Very truly, I tell you, you are looking for me, not because you saw signs, but because you ate your fill of the loaves.
43推 6:27 Do not work for the food that perishes, but for the food that endures for eternal life, which the Son of Man will give you. For it is on him that God the Father has set his seal."
43推 6:28 Then they said to him, "What must we do to perform the works of God?"
43推 6:29 Jesus answered them, "This is the work of God, that you believe in him whom he has sent."
43推 6:30 So they said to him, "What sign are you going to give us then, so that we may see it and believe you? What work are you performing?
43推 6:31 Our ancestors ate the manna in the wilderness; as it is written, 'He gave them bread from heaven to eat.'"
43推 6:32 Then Jesus said to them, "Very truly, I tell you, it was not Moses who gave you the bread from heaven, but it is my Father who gives you the true bread from heaven.
43推 6:33 For the bread of God is that which comes down from heaven and gives life to the world."
43推 6:34 They said to him, "Sir, give us this bread always."
43推 6:35 Jesus said to them, "I am the bread of life. Whoever comes to me will never be hungry, and whoever believes in me will never be thirsty.
43推 6:36 But I said to you that you have seen me and yet do not believe.
43推 6:37 Everything that the Father gives me will come to me, and anyone who comes to me I will never drive away;
43推 6:38 for I have come down from heaven, not to do my own will, but the will of him who sent me.
43推 6:39 And this is the will of him who sent me, that I should lose nothing of all that he has given me, but raise it up on the last day.
43推 6:40 This is indeed the will of my Father, that all who see the Son and believe in him may have eternal life; and I will raise them up on the last day."
43推 6:41 Then the Jews began to complain about him because he said, "I am the bread that came down from heaven."
43推 6:42 They were saying, "Is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How can he now say, 'I have come down from heaven'?"
43推 6:43 Jesus answered them, "Do not complain among yourselves.
43推 6:44 No one can come to me unless drawn by the Father who sent me; and I will raise that person up on the last day.
43推 6:45 It is written in the prophets, 'And they shall all be taught by God.' Everyone who has heard and learned from the Father comes to me.
43推 6:46 Not that anyone has seen the Father except the one who is from God; he has seen the Father.
43推 6:47 Very truly, I tell you, whoever believes has eternal life.
43推 6:48 I am the bread of life.
43推 6:49 Your ancestors ate the manna in the wilderness, and they died.
43推 6:50 This is the bread that comes down from heaven, so that one may eat of it and not die.
43推 6:51 I am the living bread that came down from heaven. Whoever eats of this bread will live forever; and the bread that I will give for the life of the world is my flesh."
43推 6:52 The Jews then disputed among themselves, saying, "How can this man give us his flesh to eat?"
43推 6:53 So Jesus said to them, "Very truly, I tell you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you have no life in you.
43推 6:54 Those who eat my flesh and drink my blood have eternal life, and I will raise them up on the last day;
43推 6:55 for my flesh is true food and my blood is true drink.
43推 6:56 Those who eat my flesh and drink my blood abide in me, and I in them.
43推 6:57 Just as the living Father sent me, and I live because of the Father, so whoever eats me will live because of me.
43推 6:58 This is the bread that came down from heaven, not like that which your ancestors ate, and they died. But the one who eats this bread will live forever."
43推 6:59 He said these things while he was teaching in the synagogue at Capernaum.
43推 6:60 When many of his disciples heard it, they said, "This teaching is difficult; who can accept it?"
43推 6:61 But Jesus, being aware that his disciples were complaining about it, said to them, "Does this offend you?
43推 6:62 Then what if you were to see the Son of Man ascending to where he was before?
43推 6:63 It is the spirit that gives life; the flesh is useless. The words that I have spoken to you are spirit and life.
43推 6:64 But among you there are some who do not believe." For Jesus knew from the first who were the ones that did not believe, and who was the one that would betray him.
43推 6:65 And he said, "For this reason I have told you that no one can come to me unless it is granted by the Father."
43推 6:66 Because of this many of his disciples turned back and no longer went about with him.
43推 6:67 So Jesus asked the twelve, "Do you also wish to go away?"
43推 6:68 Simon Peter answered him, "Lord, to whom can we go? You have the words of eternal life.
43推 6:69 We have come to believe and know that you are the Holy One of God."
43推 6:70 Jesus answered them, "Did I not choose you, the twelve? Yet one of you is a devil."
43推 6:71 He was speaking of Judas son of Simon Iscariot, for he, though one of the twelve, was going to betray him.
43推 7:1 After this Jesus went about in Galilee. He did not wish to go about in Judea because the Jews were looking for an opportunity to kill him.
43推 7:2 Now the Jewish festival of Booths was near.
43推 7:3 So his brothers said to him, "Leave here and go to Judea so that your disciples also may see the works you are doing;
43推 7:4 for no one who wants to be widely known acts in secret. If you do these things, show yourself to the world."
43推 7:5 (For not even his brothers believed in him.)
43推 7:6 Jesus said to them, "My time has not yet come, but your time is always here.
43推 7:7 The world cannot hate you, but it hates me because I testify against it that its works are evil.
43推 7:8 Go to the festival yourselves. I am not going to this festival, for my time has not yet fully come."
43推 7:9 After saying this, he remained in Galilee.
43推 7:10 But after his brothers had gone to the festival, then he also went, not publicly but as it were in secret.
43推 7:11 The Jews were looking for him at the festival and saying, "Where is he?"
43推 7:12 And there was considerable complaining about him among the crowds. While some were saying, "He is a good man," others were saying, "No, he is deceiving the crowd."
43推 7:13 Yet no one would speak openly about him for fear of the Jews.
43推 7:14 About the middle of the festival Jesus went up into the temple and began to teach.
43推 7:15 The Jews were astonished at it, saying, "How does this man have such learning, when he has never been taught?"
43推 7:16 Then Jesus answered them, "My teaching is not mine but his who sent me.
43推 7:17 Anyone who resolves to do the will of God will know whether the teaching is from God or whether I am speaking on my own.
43推 7:18 Those who speak on their own seek their own glory; but the one who seeks the glory of him who sent him is true, and there is nothing false in him.
43推 7:19 "Did not Moses give you the law? Yet none of you keeps the law. Why are you looking for an opportunity to kill me?"
43推 7:20 The crowd answered, "You have a demon! Who is trying to kill you?"
43推 7:21 Jesus answered them, "I performed one work, and all of you are astonished.
43推 7:22 Moses gave you circumcision (it is, of course, not from Moses, but from the patriarchs), and you circumcise a man on the sabbath.
43推 7:23 If a man receives circumcision on the sabbath in order that the law of Moses may not be broken, are you angry with me because I healed a man's whole body on the sabbath?
43推 7:24 Do not judge by appearances, but judge with right judgment."
43推 7:25 Now some of the people of Jerusalem were saying, "Is not this the man whom they are trying to kill?
43推 7:26 And here he is, speaking openly, but they say nothing to him! Can it be that the authorities really know that this is the Messiah?
43推 7:27 Yet we know where this man is from; but when the Messiah comes, no one will know where he is from."
43推 7:28 Then Jesus cried out as he was teaching in the temple, "You know me, and you know where I am from. I have not come on my own. But the one who sent me is true, and you do not know him.
43推 7:29 I know him, because I am from him, and he sent me."
43推 7:30 Then they tried to arrest him, but no one laid hands on him, because his hour had not yet come.
43推 7:31 Yet many in the crowd believed in him and were saying, "When the Messiah comes, will he do more signs than this man has done?"
43推 7:32 The Pharisees heard the crowd muttering such things about him, and the chief priests and Pharisees sent temple police to arrest him.
43推 7:33 Jesus then said, "I will be with you a little while longer, and then I am going to him who sent me.
43推 7:34 You will search for me, but you will not find me; and where I am, you cannot come."
43推 7:35 The Jews said to one another, "Where does this man intend to go that we will not find him? Does he intend to go to the Dispersion among the Greeks and teach the Greeks?
43推 7:36 What does he mean by saying, 'You will search for me and you will not find me' and 'Where I am, you cannot come'?"
43推 7:37 On the last day of the festival, the great day, while Jesus was standing there, he cried out, "Let anyone who is thirsty come to me,
43推 7:38 and let the one who believes in me drink. As the scripture has said, 'Out of the believer's heart shall flow rivers of living water.'"
43推 7:39 Now he said this about the Spirit, which believers in him were to receive; for as yet there was no Spirit, because Jesus was not yet glorified.
43推 7:40 When they heard these words, some in the crowd said, "This is really the prophet."
43推 7:41 Others said, "This is the Messiah." But some asked, "Surely the Messiah does not come from Galilee, does he?
43推 7:42 Has not the scripture said that the Messiah is descended from David and comes from Bethlehem, the village where David lived?"
43推 7:43 So there was a division in the crowd because of him.
43推 7:44 Some of them wanted to arrest him, but no one laid hands on him.
43推 7:45 Then the temple police went back to the chief priests and Pharisees, who asked them, "Why did you not arrest him?"
43推 7:46 The police answered, "Never has anyone spoken like this!"
43推 7:47 Then the Pharisees replied, "Surely you have not been deceived too, have you?
43推 7:48 Has any one of the authorities or of the Pharisees believed in him?
43推 7:49 But this crowd, which does not know the law--they are accursed."
43推 7:50 Nicodemus, who had gone to Jesus before, and who was one of them, asked,
43推 7:51 "Our law does not judge people without first giving them a hearing to find out what they are doing, does it?"
43推 7:52 They replied, "Surely you are not also from Galilee, are you? Search and you will see that no prophet is to arise from Galilee."
43推 7:53 Then each of them went home,
43推 8:1 while Jesus went to the Mount of Olives.
43推 8:2 Early in the morning he came again to the temple. All the people came to him and he sat down and began to teach them.
43推 8:3 The scribes and the Pharisees brought a woman who had been caught in adultery; and making her stand before all of them,
43推 8:4 they said to him, "Teacher, this woman was caught in the very act of committing adultery.
43推 8:5 Now in the law Moses commanded us to stone such women. Now what do you say?"
43推 8:6 They said this to test him, so that they might have some charge to bring against him. Jesus bent down and wrote with his finger on the ground.
43推 8:7 When they kept on questioning him, he straightened up and said to them, "Let anyone among you who is without sin be the first to throw a stone at her."
43推 8:8 And once again he bent down and wrote on the ground.
43推 8:9 When they heard it, they went away, one by one, beginning with the elders; and Jesus was left alone with the woman standing before him.
43推 8:10 Jesus straightened up and said to her, "Woman, where are they? Has no one condemned you?"
43推 8:11 She said, "No one, sir." And Jesus said, "Neither do I condemn you. Go your way, and from now on do not sin again."
43推 8:12 Again Jesus spoke to them, saying, "I am the light of the world. Whoever follows me will never walk in darkness but will have the light of life."
43推 8:13 Then the Pharisees said to him, "You are testifying on your own behalf; your testimony is not valid."
43推 8:14 Jesus answered, "Even if I testify on my own behalf, my testimony is valid because I know where I have come from and where I am going, but you do not know where I come from or where I am going.
43推 8:15 You judge by human standards; I judge no one.
43推 8:16 Yet even if I do judge, my judgment is valid; for it is not I alone who judge, but I and the Father who sent me.
43推 8:17 In your law it is written that the testimony of two witnesses is valid.
43推 8:18 I testify on my own behalf, and the Father who sent me testifies on my behalf."
43推 8:19 Then they said to him, "Where is your Father?" Jesus answered, "You know neither me nor my Father. If you knew me, you would know my Father also."
43推 8:20 He spoke these words while he was teaching in the treasury of the temple, but no one arrested him, because his hour had not yet come.
43推 8:21 Again he said to them, "I am going away, and you will search for me, but you will die in your sin. Where I am going, you cannot come."
43推 8:22 Then the Jews said, "Is he going to kill himself? Is that what he means by saying, 'Where I am going, you cannot come'?"
43推 8:23 He said to them, "You are from below, I am from above; you are of this world, I am not of this world.
43推 8:24 I told you that you would die in your sins, for you will die in your sins unless you believe that I am he."
43推 8:25 They said to him, "Who are you?" Jesus said to them, "Why do I speak to you at all?
43推 8:26 I have much to say about you and much to condemn; but the one who sent me is true, and I declare to the world what I have heard from him."
43推 8:27 They did not understand that he was speaking to them about the Father.
43推 8:28 So Jesus said, "When you have lifted up the Son of Man, then you will realize that I am he, and that I do nothing on my own, but I speak these things as the Father instructed me.
43推 8:29 And the one who sent me is with me; he has not left me alone, for I always do what is pleasing to him."
43推 8:30 As he was saying these things, many believed in him.
43推 8:31 Then Jesus said to the Jews who had believed in him, "If you continue in my word, you are truly my disciples;
43推 8:32 and you will know the truth, and the truth will make you free."
43推 8:33 They answered him, "We are descendants of Abraham and have never been slaves to anyone. What do you mean by saying, 'You will be made free'?"
43推 8:34 Jesus answered them, "Very truly, I tell you, everyone who commits sin is a slave to sin.
43推 8:35 The slave does not have a permanent place in the household; the son has a place there forever.
43推 8:36 So if the Son makes you free, you will be free indeed.
43推 8:37 I know that you are descendants of Abraham; yet you look for an opportunity to kill me, because there is no place in you for my word.
43推 8:38 I declare what I have seen in the Father's presence; as for you, you should do what you have heard from the Father."
43推 8:39 They answered him, "Abraham is our father." Jesus said to them, "If you were Abraham's children, you would be doing what Abraham did,
43推 8:40 but now you are trying to kill me, a man who has told you the truth that I heard from God. This is not what Abraham did.
43推 8:41 You are indeed doing what your father does." They said to him, "We are not illegitimate children; we have one father, God himself."
43推 8:42 Jesus said to them, "If God were your Father, you would love me, for I came from God and now I am here. I did not come on my own, but he sent me.
43推 8:43 Why do you not understand what I say? It is because you cannot accept my word.
43推 8:44 You are from your father the devil, and you choose to do your father's desires. He was a murderer from the beginning and does not stand in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he lies, he speaks according to his own nature, for he is a liar and the father of lies.
43推 8:45 But because I tell the truth, you do not believe me.
43推 8:46 Which of you convicts me of sin? If I tell the truth, why do you not believe me?
43推 8:47 Whoever is from God hears the words of God. The reason you do not hear them is that you are not from God."
43推 8:48 The Jews answered him, "Are we not right in saying that you are a Samaritan and have a demon?"
43推 8:49 Jesus answered, "I do not have a demon; but I honor my Father, and you dishonor me.
43推 8:50 Yet I do not seek my own glory; there is one who seeks it and he is the judge.
43推 8:51 Very truly, I tell you, whoever keeps my word will never see death."
43推 8:52 The Jews said to him, "Now we know that you have a demon. Abraham died, and so did the prophets; yet you say, 'Whoever keeps my word will never taste death.'
43推 8:53 Are you greater than our father Abraham, who died? The prophets also died. Who do you claim to be?"
43推 8:54 Jesus answered, "If I glorify myself, my glory is nothing. It is my Father who glorifies me, he of whom you say, 'He is our God,'
43推 8:55 though you do not know him. But I know him; if I would say that I do not know him, I would be a liar like you. But I do know him and I keep his word.
43推 8:56 Your ancestor Abraham rejoiced that he would see my day; he saw it and was glad."
43推 8:57 Then the Jews said to him, "You are not yet fifty years old, and have you seen Abraham?"
43推 8:58 Jesus said to them, "Very truly, I tell you, before Abraham was, I am."
43推 8:59 So they picked up stones to throw at him, but Jesus hid himself and went out of the temple.
43推 9:1 As he walked along, he saw a man blind from birth.
43推 9:2 His disciples asked him, "Rabbi, who sinned, this man or his parents, that he was born blind?"
43推 9:3 Jesus answered, "Neither this man nor his parents sinned; he was born blind so that God's works might be revealed in him.
43推 9:4 We must work the works of him who sent me while it is day; night is coming when no one can work.
43推 9:5 As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world."
43推 9:6 When he had said this, he spat on the ground and made mud with the saliva and spread the mud on the man's eyes,
43推 9:7 saying to him, "Go, wash in the pool of Siloam" (which means Sent). Then he went and washed and came back able to see.
43推 9:8 The neighbors and those who had seen him before as a beggar began to ask, "Is this not the man who used to sit and beg?"
43推 9:9 Some were saying, "It is he." Others were saying, "No, but it is someone like him." He kept saying, "I am the man."
43推 9:10 But they kept asking him, "Then how were your eyes opened?"
43推 9:11 He answered, "The man called Jesus made mud, spread it on my eyes, and said to me, 'Go to Siloam and wash.' Then I went and washed and received my sight."
43推 9:12 They said to him, "Where is he?" He said, "I do not know."
43推 9:13 They brought to the Pharisees the man who had formerly been blind.
43推 9:14 Now it was a sabbath day when Jesus made the mud and opened his eyes.
43推 9:15 Then the Pharisees also began to ask him how he had received his sight. He said to them, "He put mud on my eyes. Then I washed, and now I see."
43推 9:16 Some of the Pharisees said, "This man is not from God, for he does not observe the sabbath." But others said, "How can a man who is a sinner perform such signs?" And they were divided.
43推 9:17 So they said again to the blind man, "What do you say about him? It was your eyes he opened." He said, "He is a prophet."
43推 9:18 The Jews did not believe that he had been blind and had received his sight until they called the parents of the man who had received his sight
43推 9:19 and asked them, "Is this your son, who you say was born blind? How then does he now see?"
43推 9:20 His parents answered, "We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind;
43推 9:21 but we do not know how it is that now he sees, nor do we know who opened his eyes. Ask him; he is of age. He will speak for himself."
43推 9:22 His parents said this because they were afraid of the Jews; for the Jews had already agreed that anyone who confessed Jesus to be the Messiah would be put out of the synagogue.
43推 9:23 Therefore his parents said, "He is of age; ask him."
43推 9:24 So for the second time they called the man who had been blind, and they said to him, "Give glory to God! We know that this man is a sinner."
43推 9:25 He answered, "I do not know whether he is a sinner. One thing I do know, that though I was blind, now I see."
43推 9:26 They said to him, "What did he do to you? How did he open your eyes?"
43推 9:27 He answered them, "I have told you already, and you would not listen. Why do you want to hear it again? Do you also want to become his disciples?"
43推 9:28 Then they reviled him, saying, "You are his disciple, but we are disciples of Moses.
43推 9:29 We know that God has spoken to Moses, but as for this man, we do not know where he comes from."
43推 9:30 The man answered, "Here is an astonishing thing! You do not know where he comes from, and yet he opened my eyes.
43推 9:31 We know that God does not listen to sinners, but he does listen to one who worships him and obeys his will.
43推 9:32 Never since the world began has it been heard that anyone opened the eyes of a person born blind.
43推 9:33 If this man were not from God, he could do nothing."
43推 9:34 They answered him, "You were born entirely in sins, and are you trying to teach us?" And they drove him out.
43推 9:35 Jesus heard that they had driven him out, and when he found him, he said, "Do you believe in the Son of Man?"
43推 9:36 He answered, "And who is he, sir? Tell me, so that I may believe in him."
43推 9:37 Jesus said to him, "You have seen him, and the one speaking with you is he."
43推 9:38 He said, "Lord, I believe." And he worshiped him.
43推 9:39 Jesus said, "I came into this world for judgment so that those who do not see may see, and those who do see may become blind."
43推 9:40 Some of the Pharisees near him heard this and said to him, "Surely we are not blind, are we?"
43推 9:41 Jesus said to them, "If you were blind, you would not have sin. But now that you say, 'We see,' your sin remains.
43推 10:1 "Very truly, I tell you, anyone who does not enter the sheepfold by the gate but climbs in by another way is a thief and a bandit.
43推 10:2 The one who enters by the gate is the shepherd of the sheep.
43推 10:3 The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, and the sheep hear his voice. He calls his own sheep by name and leads them out.
43推 10:4 When he has brought out all his own, he goes ahead of them, and the sheep follow him because they know his voice.
43推 10:5 They will not follow a stranger, but they will run from him because they do not know the voice of strangers."
43推 10:6 Jesus used this figure of speech with them, but they did not understand what he was saying to them.
43推 10:7 So again Jesus said to them, "Very truly, I tell you, I am the gate for the sheep.
43推 10:8 All who came before me are thieves and bandits; but the sheep did not listen to them.
43推 10:9 I am the gate. Whoever enters by me will be saved, and will come in and go out and find pasture.
43推 10:10 The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy. I came that they may have life, and have it abundantly.
43推 10:11 "I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.
43推 10:12 The hired hand, who is not the shepherd and does not own the sheep, sees the wolf coming and leaves the sheep and runs away--and the wolf snatches them and scatters them.
43推 10:13 The hired hand runs away because a hired hand does not care for the sheep.
43推 10:14 I am the good shepherd. I know my own and my own know me,
43推 10:15 just as the Father knows me and I know the Father. And I lay down my life for the sheep.
43推 10:16 I have other sheep that do not belong to this fold. I must bring them also, and they will listen to my voice. So there will be one flock, one shepherd.
43推 10:17 For this reason the Father loves me, because I lay down my life in order to take it up again.
43推 10:18 No one takes it from me, but I lay it down of my own accord. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it up again. I have received this command from my Father."
43推 10:19 Again the Jews were divided because of these words.
43推 10:20 Many of them were saying, "He has a demon and is out of his mind. Why listen to him?"
43推 10:21 Others were saying, "These are not the words of one who has a demon. Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?"
43推 10:22 At that time the festival of the Dedication took place in Jerusalem. It was winter,
43推 10:23 and Jesus was walking in the temple, in the portico of Solomon.
43推 10:24 So the Jews gathered around him and said to him, "How long will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Messiah, tell us plainly."
43推 10:25 Jesus answered, "I have told you, and you do not believe. The works that I do in my Father's name testify to me;
43推 10:26 but you do not believe, because you do not belong to my sheep.
43推 10:27 My sheep hear my voice. I know them, and they follow me.
43推 10:28 I give them eternal life, and they will never perish. No one will snatch them out of my hand.
43推 10:29 What my Father has given me is greater than all else, and no one can snatch it out of the Father's hand.
43推 10:30 The Father and I are one."
43推 10:31 The Jews took up stones again to stone him.
43推 10:32 Jesus replied, "I have shown you many good works from the Father. For which of these are you going to stone me?"
43推 10:33 The Jews answered, "It is not for a good work that we are going to stone you, but for blasphemy, because you, though only a human being, are making yourself God."
43推 10:34 Jesus answered, "Is it not written in your law, 'I said, you are gods'?
43推 10:35 If those to whom the word of God came were called 'gods'--and the scripture cannot be annulled--
43推 10:36 can you say that the one whom the Father has sanctified and sent into the world is blaspheming because I said, 'I am God's Son'?
43推 10:37 If I am not doing the works of my Father, then do not believe me.
43推 10:38 But if I do them, even though you do not believe me, believe the works, so that you may know and understand that the Father is in me and I am in the Father."
43推 10:39 Then they tried to arrest him again, but he escaped from their hands.
43推 10:40 He went away again across the Jordan to the place where John had been baptizing earlier, and he remained there.
43推 10:41 Many came to him, and they were saying, "John performed no sign, but everything that John said about this man was true."
43推 10:42 And many believed in him there.
43推 11:1 Now a certain man was ill, Lazarus of Bethany, the village of Mary and her sister Martha.
43推 11:2 Mary was the one who anointed the Lord with perfume and wiped his feet with her hair; her brother Lazarus was ill.
43推 11:3 So the sisters sent a message to Jesus, "Lord, he whom you love is ill."
43推 11:4 But when Jesus heard it, he said, "This illness does not lead to death; rather it is for God's glory, so that the Son of God may be glorified through it."
43推 11:5 Accordingly, though Jesus loved Martha and her sister and Lazarus,
43推 11:6 after having heard that Lazarus was ill, he stayed two days longer in the place where he was.
43推 11:7 Then after this he said to the disciples, "Let us go to Judea again."
43推 11:8 The disciples said to him, "Rabbi, the Jews were just now trying to stone you, and are you going there again?"
43推 11:9 Jesus answered, "Are there not twelve hours of daylight? Those who walk during the day do not stumble, because they see the light of this world.
43推 11:10 But those who walk at night stumble, because the light is not in them."
43推 11:11 After saying this, he told them, "Our friend Lazarus has fallen asleep, but I am going there to awaken him."
43推 11:12 The disciples said to him, "Lord, if he has fallen asleep, he will be all right."
43推 11:13 Jesus, however, had been speaking about his death, but they thought that he was referring merely to sleep.
43推 11:14 Then Jesus told them plainly, "Lazarus is dead.
43推 11:15 For your sake I am glad I was not there, so that you may believe. But let us go to him."
43推 11:16 Thomas, who was called the Twin, said to his fellow disciples, "Let us also go, that we may die with him."
43推 11:17 When Jesus arrived, he found that Lazarus had already been in the tomb four days.
43推 11:18 Now Bethany was near Jerusalem, some two miles away,
43推 11:19 and many of the Jews had come to Martha and Mary to console them about their brother.
43推 11:20 When Martha heard that Jesus was coming, she went and met him, while Mary stayed at home.
43推 11:21 Martha said to Jesus, "Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died.
43推 11:22 But even now I know that God will give you whatever you ask of him."
43推 11:23 Jesus said to her, "Your brother will rise again."
43推 11:24 Martha said to him, "I know that he will rise again in the resurrection on the last day."
43推 11:25 Jesus said to her, "I am the resurrection and the life. Those who believe in me, even though they die, will live,
43推 11:26 and everyone who lives and believes in me will never die. Do you believe this?"
43推 11:27 She said to him, "Yes, Lord, I believe that you are the Messiah, the Son of God, the one coming into the world."
43推 11:28 When she had said this, she went back and called her sister Mary, and told her privately, "The Teacher is here and is calling for you."
43推 11:29 And when she heard it, she got up quickly and went to him.
43推 11:30 Now Jesus had not yet come to the village, but was still at the place where Martha had met him.
43推 11:31 The Jews who were with her in the house, consoling her, saw Mary get up quickly and go out. They followed her because they thought that she was going to the tomb to weep there.
43推 11:32 When Mary came where Jesus was and saw him, she knelt at his feet and said to him, "Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died."
43推 11:33 When Jesus saw her weeping, and the Jews who came with her also weeping, he was greatly disturbed in spirit and deeply moved.
43推 11:34 He said, "Where have you laid him?" They said to him, "Lord, come and see."
43推 11:35 Jesus began to weep.
43推 11:36 So the Jews said, "See how he loved him!"
43推 11:37 But some of them said, "Could not he who opened the eyes of the blind man have kept this man from dying?"
43推 11:38 Then Jesus, again greatly disturbed, came to the tomb. It was a cave, and a stone was lying against it.
43推 11:39 Jesus said, "Take away the stone." Martha, the sister of the dead man, said to him, "Lord, already there is a stench because he has been dead four days."
43推 11:40 Jesus said to her, "Did I not tell you that if you believed, you would see the glory of God?"
43推 11:41 So they took away the stone. And Jesus looked upward and said, "Father, I thank you for having heard me.
43推 11:42 I knew that you always hear me, but I have said this for the sake of the crowd standing here, so that they may believe that you sent me."
43推 11:43 When he had said this, he cried with a loud voice, "Lazarus, come out!"
43推 11:44 The dead man came out, his hands and feet bound with strips of cloth, and his face wrapped in a cloth. Jesus said to them, "Unbind him, and let him go."
43推 11:45 Many of the Jews therefore, who had come with Mary and had seen what Jesus did, believed in him.
43推 11:46 But some of them went to the Pharisees and told them what he had done.
43推 11:47 So the chief priests and the Pharisees called a meeting of the council, and said, "What are we to do? This man is performing many signs.
43推 11:48 If we let him go on like this, everyone will believe in him, and the Romans will come and destroy both our holy place and our nation."
43推 11:49 But one of them, Caiaphas, who was high priest that year, said to them, "You know nothing at all!
43推 11:50 You do not understand that it is better for you to have one man die for the people than to have the whole nation destroyed."
43推 11:51 He did not say this on his own, but being high priest that year he prophesied that Jesus was about to die for the nation,
43推 11:52 and not for the nation only, but to gather into one the dispersed children of God.
43推 11:53 So from that day on they planned to put him to death.
43推 11:54 Jesus therefore no longer walked about openly among the Jews, but went from there to a town called Ephraim in the region near the wilderness; and he remained there with the disciples.
43推 11:55 Now the Passover of the Jews was near, and many went up from the country to Jerusalem before the Passover to purify themselves.
43推 11:56 They were looking for Jesus and were asking one another as they stood in the temple, "What do you think? Surely he will not come to the festival, will he?"
43推 11:57 Now the chief priests and the Pharisees had given orders that anyone who knew where Jesus was should let them know, so that they might arrest him.
43推 12:1 Six days before the Passover Jesus came to Bethany, the home of Lazarus, whom he had raised from the dead.
43推 12:2 There they gave a dinner for him. Martha served, and Lazarus was one of those at the table with him.
43推 12:3 Mary took a pound of costly perfume made of pure nard, anointed Jesus' feet, and wiped them with her hair. The house was filled with the fragrance of the perfume.
43推 12:4 But Judas Iscariot, one of his disciples (the one who was about to betray him), said,
43推 12:5 "Why was this perfume not sold for three hundred denarii and the money given to the poor?"
43推 12:6 (He said this not because he cared about the poor, but because he was a thief; he kept the common purse and used to steal what was put into it.)
43推 12:7 Jesus said, "Leave her alone. She bought it so that she might keep it for the day of my burial.
43推 12:8 You always have the poor with you, but you do not always have me."
43推 12:9 When the great crowd of the Jews learned that he was there, they came not only because of Jesus but also to see Lazarus, whom he had raised from the dead.
43推 12:10 So the chief priests planned to put Lazarus to death as well,
43推 12:11 since it was on account of him that many of the Jews were deserting and were believing in Jesus.
43推 12:12 The next day the great crowd that had come to the festival heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem.
43推 12:13 So they took branches of palm trees and went out to meet him, shouting, "Hosanna! Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord--the King of Israel!"
43推 12:14 Jesus found a young donkey and sat on it; as it is written:
43推 12:15 "Do not be afraid, daughter of Zion. Look, your king is coming, sitting on a donkey's colt!"
43推 12:16 His disciples did not understand these things at first; but when Jesus was glorified, then they remembered that these things had been written of him and had been done to him.
43推 12:17 So the crowd that had been with him when he called Lazarus out of the tomb and raised him from the dead continued to testify.
43推 12:18 It was also because they heard that he had performed this sign that the crowd went to meet him.
43推 12:19 The Pharisees then said to one another, "You see, you can do nothing. Look, the world has gone after him!"
43推 12:20 Now among those who went up to worship at the festival were some Greeks.
43推 12:21 They came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee, and said to him, "Sir, we wish to see Jesus."
43推 12:22 Philip went and told Andrew; then Andrew and Philip went and told Jesus.
43推 12:23 Jesus answered them, "The hour has come for the Son of Man to be glorified.
43推 12:24 Very truly, I tell you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains just a single grain; but if it dies, it bears much fruit.
43推 12:25 Those who love their life lose it, and those who hate their life in this world will keep it for eternal life.
43推 12:26 Whoever serves me must follow me, and where I am, there will my servant be also. Whoever serves me, the Father will honor.
43推 12:27 "Now my soul is troubled. And what should I say--'Father, save me from this hour'? No, it is for this reason that I have come to this hour.
43推 12:28 Father, glorify your name.'' Then a voice came from heaven, "I have glorified it, and I will glorify it again."
43推 12:29 The crowd standing there heard it and said that it was thunder. Others said, "An angel has spoken to him."
43推 12:30 Jesus answered, "This voice has come for your sake, not for mine.
43推 12:31 Now is the judgment of this world; now the ruler of this world will be driven out.
43推 12:32 And I, when I am lifted up from the earth, will draw all people to myself."
43推 12:33 He said this to indicate the kind of death he was to die.
43推 12:34 The crowd answered him, "We have heard from the law that the Messiah remains forever. How can you say that the Son of Man must be lifted up? Who is this Son of Man?"
43推 12:35 Jesus said to them, "The light is with you for a little longer. Walk while you have the light, so that the darkness may not overtake you. If you walk in the darkness, you do not know where you are going.
43推 12:36 While you have the light, believe in the light, so that you may become children of light." After Jesus had said this, he departed and hid from them.
43推 12:37 Although he had performed so many signs in their presence, they did not believe in him.
43推 12:38 This was to fulfill the word spoken by the prophet Isaiah: "Lord, who has believed our message, and to whom has the arm of the Lord been revealed?"
43推 12:39 And so they could not believe, because Isaiah also said,
43推 12:40 "He has blinded their eyes and hardened their heart, so that they might not look with their eyes, and understand with their heart and turn--and I would heal them."
43推 12:41 Isaiah said this because he saw his glory and spoke about him.
43推 12:42 Nevertheless many, even of the authorities, believed in him. But because of the Pharisees they did not confess it, for fear that they would be put out of the synagogue;
43推 12:43 for they loved human glory more than the glory that comes from God.
43推 12:44 Then Jesus cried aloud: "Whoever believes in me believes not in me but in him who sent me.
43推 12:45 And whoever sees me sees him who sent me.
43推 12:46 I have come as light into the world, so that everyone who believes in me should not remain in the darkness.
43推 12:47 I do not judge anyone who hears my words and does not keep them, for I came not to judge the world, but to save the world.
43推 12:48 The one who rejects me and does not receive my word has a judge; on the last day the word that I have spoken will serve as judge,
43推 12:49 for I have not spoken on my own, but the Father who sent me has himself given me a commandment about what to say and what to speak.
43推 12:50 And I know that his commandment is eternal life. What I speak, therefore, I speak just as the Father has told me."
43推 13:1 Now before the festival of the Passover, Jesus knew that his hour had come to depart from this world and go to the Father. Having loved his own who were in the world, he loved them to the end.
43推 13:2 The devil had already put it into the heart of Judas son of Simon Iscariot to betray him. And during supper
43推 13:3 Jesus, knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that he had come from God and was going to God,
43推 13:4 got up from the table, took off his outer robe, and tied a towel around himself.
43推 13:5 Then he poured water into a basin and began to wash the disciples' feet and to wipe them with the towel that was tied around him.
43推 13:6 He came to Simon Peter, who said to him, "Lord, are you going to wash my feet?"
43推 13:7 Jesus answered, "You do not know now what I am doing, but later you will understand."
43推 13:8 Peter said to him, "You will never wash my feet." Jesus answered, "Unless I wash you, you have no share with me."
43推 13:9 Simon Peter said to him, "Lord, not my feet only but also my hands and my head!"
43推 13:10 Jesus said to him, "One who has bathed does not need to wash, except for the feet, but is entirely clean. And you are clean, though not all of you."
43推 13:11 For he knew who was to betray him; for this reason he said, "Not all of you are clean."
43推 13:12 After he had washed their feet, had put on his robe, and had returned to the table, he said to them, "Do you know what I have done to you?
43推 13:13 You call me Teacher and Lord--and you are right, for that is what I am.
43推 13:14 So if I, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you also ought to wash one another's feet.
43推 13:15 For I have set you an example, that you also should do as I have done to you.
43推 13:16 Very truly, I tell you, servants are not greater than their master, nor are messengers greater than the one who sent them.
43推 13:17 If you know these things, you are blessed if you do them.
43推 13:18 I am not speaking of all of you; I know whom I have chosen. But it is to fulfill the scripture, 'The one who ate my bread has lifted his heel against me.'
43推 13:19 I tell you this now, before it occurs, so that when it does occur, you may believe that I am he.
43推 13:20 Very truly, I tell you, whoever receives one whom I send receives me; and whoever receives me receives him who sent me."
43推 13:21 After saying this Jesus was troubled in spirit, and declared, "Very truly, I tell you, one of you will betray me."
43推 13:22 The disciples looked at one another, uncertain of whom he was speaking.
43推 13:23 One of his disciples--the one whom Jesus loved--was reclining next to him;
43推 13:24 Simon Peter therefore motioned to him to ask Jesus of whom he was speaking.
43推 13:25 So while reclining next to Jesus, he asked him, "Lord, who is it?"
43推 13:26 Jesus answered, "It is the one to whom I give this piece of bread when I have dipped it in the dish." So when he had dipped the piece of bread, he gave it to Judas son of Simon Iscariot.
43推 13:27 After he received the piece of bread, Satan entered into him. Jesus said to him, "Do quickly what you are going to do."
43推 13:28 Now no one at the table knew why he said this to him.
43推 13:29 Some thought that, because Judas had the common purse, Jesus was telling him, "Buy what we need for the festival"; or, that he should give something to the poor.
43推 13:30 So, after receiving the piece of bread, he immediately went out. And it was night.
43推 13:31 When he had gone out, Jesus said, "Now the Son of Man has been glorified, and God has been glorified in him.
43推 13:32 If God has been glorified in him, God will also glorify him in himself and will glorify him at once.
43推 13:33 Little children, I am with you only a little longer. You will look for me; and as I said to the Jews so now I say to you, 'Where I am going, you cannot come.'
43推 13:34 I give you a new commandment, that you love one another. Just as I have loved you, you also should love one another.
43推 13:35 By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you have love for one another."
43推 13:36 Simon Peter said to him, "Lord, where are you going?" Jesus answered, "Where I am going, you cannot follow me now; but you will follow afterward."
43推 13:37 Peter said to him, "Lord, why can I not follow you now? I will lay down my life for you."
43推 13:38 Jesus answered, "Will you lay down your life for me? Very truly, I tell you, before the cock crows, you will have denied me three times.
43推 14:1 "Do not let your hearts be troubled. Believe in God, believe also in me.
43推 14:2 In my Father's house there are many dwelling places. If it were not so, would I have told you that I go to prepare a place for you?
43推 14:3 And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again and will take you to myself, so that where I am, there you may be also.
43推 14:4 And you know the way to the place where I am going."
43推 14:5 Thomas said to him, "Lord, we do not know where you are going. How can we know the way?"
43推 14:6 Jesus said to him, "I am the way, and the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me.
43推 14:7 If you know me, you will know my Father also. From now on you do know him and have seen him."
43推 14:8 Philip said to him, "Lord, show us the Father, and we will be satisfied."
43推 14:9 Jesus said to him, "Have I been with you all this time, Philip, and you still do not know me? Whoever has seen me has seen the Father. How can you say, 'Show us the Father'?
43推 14:10 Do you not believe that I am in the Father and the Father is in me? The words that I say to you I do not speak on my own; but the Father who dwells in me does his works.
43推 14:11 Believe me that I am in the Father and the Father is in me; but if you do not, then believe me because of the works themselves.
43推 14:12 Very truly, I tell you, the one who believes in me will also do the works that I do and, in fact, will do greater works than these, because I am going to the Father.
43推 14:13 I will do whatever you ask in my name, so that the Father may be glorified in the Son.
43推 14:14 If in my name you ask me for anything, I will do it.
43推 14:15 "If you love me, you will keep my commandments.
43推 14:16 And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another Advocate, to be with you forever.
43推 14:17 This is the Spirit of truth, whom the world cannot receive, because it neither sees him nor knows him. You know him, because he abides with you, and he will be in you.
43推 14:18 "I will not leave you orphaned; I am coming to you.
43推 14:19 In a little while the world will no longer see me, but you will see me; because I live, you also will live.
43推 14:20 On that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.
43推 14:21 They who have my commandments and keep them are those who love me; and those who love me will be loved by my Father, and I will love them and reveal myself to them."
43推 14:22 Judas (not Iscariot) said to him, "Lord, how is it that you will reveal yourself to us, and not to the world?"
43推 14:23 Jesus answered him, "Those who love me will keep my word, and my Father will love them, and we will come to them and make our home with them.
43推 14:24 Whoever does not love me does not keep my words; and the word that you hear is not mine, but is from the Father who sent me.
43推 14:25 "I have said these things to you while I am still with you.
43推 14:26 But the Advocate, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, will teach you everything, and remind you of all that I have said to you.
43推 14:27 Peace I leave with you; my peace I give to you. I do not give to you as the world gives. Do not let your hearts be troubled, and do not let them be afraid.
43推 14:28 You heard me say to you, 'I am going away, and I am coming to you.' If you loved me, you would rejoice that I am going to the Father, because the Father is greater than I.
43推 14:29 And now I have told you this before it occurs, so that when it does occur, you may believe.
43推 14:30 I will no longer talk much with you, for the ruler of this world is coming. He has no power over me;
43推 14:31 but I do as the Father has commanded me, so that the world may know that I love the Father. Rise, let us be on our way.
43推 15:1 "I am the true vine, and my Father is the vinegrower.
43推 15:2 He removes every branch in me that bears no fruit. Every branch that bears fruit he prunes to make it bear more fruit.
43推 15:3 You have already been cleansed by the word that I have spoken to you.
43推 15:4 Abide in me as I abide in you. Just as the branch cannot bear fruit by itself unless it abides in the vine, neither can you unless you abide in me.
43推 15:5 I am the vine, you are the branches. Those who abide in me and I in them bear much fruit, because apart from me you can do nothing.
43推 15:6 Whoever does not abide in me is thrown away like a branch and withers; such branches are gathered, thrown into the fire, and burned.
43推 15:7 If you abide in me, and my words abide in you, ask for whatever you wish, and it will be done for you.
43推 15:8 My Father is glorified by this, that you bear much fruit and become my disciples.
43推 15:9 As the Father has loved me, so I have loved you; abide in my love.
43推 15:10 If you keep my commandments, you will abide in my love, just as I have kept my Father's commandments and abide in his love.
43推 15:11 I have said these things to you so that my joy may be in you, and that your joy may be complete.
43推 15:12 "This is my commandment, that you love one another as I have loved you.
43推 15:13 No one has greater love than this, to lay down one's life for one's friends.
43推 15:14 You are my friends if you do what I command you.
43推 15:15 I do not call you servants any longer, because the servant does not know what the master is doing; but I have called you friends, because I have made known to you everything that I have heard from my Father.
43推 15:16 You did not choose me but I chose you. And I appointed you to go and bear fruit, fruit that will last, so that the Father will give you whatever you ask him in my name.
43推 15:17 I am giving you these commands so that you may love one another.
43推 15:18 "If the world hates you, be aware that it hated me before it hated you.
43推 15:19 If you belonged to the world, the world would love you as its own. Because you do not belong to the world, but I have chosen you out of the world--therefore the world hates you.
43推 15:20 Remember the word that I said to you, 'Servants are not greater than their master.' If they persecuted me, they will persecute you; if they kept my word, they will keep yours also.
43推 15:21 But they will do all these things to you on account of my name, because they do not know him who sent me.
43推 15:22 If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have sin; but now they have no excuse for their sin.
43推 15:23 Whoever hates me hates my Father also.
43推 15:24 If I had not done among them the works that no one else did, they would not have sin. But now they have seen and hated both me and my Father.
43推 15:25 It was to fulfill the word that is written in their law, 'They hated me without a cause.'
43推 15:26 "When the Advocate comes, whom I will send to you from the Father, the Spirit of truth who comes from the Father, he will testify on my behalf.
43推 15:27 You also are to testify because you have been with me from the beginning.
43推 16:1 "I have said these things to you to keep you from stumbling.
43推 16:2 They will put you out of the synagogues. Indeed, an hour is coming when those who kill you will think that by doing so they are offering worship to God.
43推 16:3 And they will do this because they have not known the Father or me.
43推 16:4 But I have said these things to you so that when their hour comes you may remember that I told you about them. "I did not say these things to you from the beginning, because I was with you.
43推 16:5 But now I am going to him who sent me; yet none of you asks me, 'Where are you going?'
43推 16:6 But because I have said these things to you, sorrow has filled your hearts.
43推 16:7 Nevertheless I tell you the truth: it is to your advantage that I go away, for if I do not go away, the Advocate will not come to you; but if I go, I will send him to you.
43推 16:8 And when he comes, he will prove the world wrong about sin and righteousness and judgment:
43推 16:9 about sin, because they do not believe in me;
43推 16:10 about righteousness, because I am going to the Father and you will see me no longer;
43推 16:11 about judgment, because the ruler of this world has been condemned.
43推 16:12 "I still have many things to say to you, but you cannot bear them now.
43推 16:13 When the Spirit of truth comes, he will guide you into all the truth; for he will not speak on his own, but will speak whatever he hears, and he will declare to you the things that are to come.
43推 16:14 He will glorify me, because he will take what is mine and declare it to you.
43推 16:15 All that the Father has is mine. For this reason I said that he will take what is mine and declare it to you.
43推 16:16 "A little while, and you will no longer see me, and again a little while, and you will see me."
43推 16:17 Then some of his disciples said to one another, "What does he mean by saying to us, 'A little while, and you will no longer see me, and again a little while, and you will see me'; and 'Because I am going to the Father'?"
43推 16:18 They said, "What does he mean by this 'a little while'? We do not know what he is talking about."
43推 16:19 Jesus knew that they wanted to ask him, so he said to them, "Are you discussing among yourselves what I meant when I said, 'A little while, and you will no longer see me, and again a little while, and you will see me'?
43推 16:20 Very truly, I tell you, you will weep and mourn, but the world will rejoice; you will have pain, but your pain will turn into joy.
43推 16:21 When a woman is in labor, she has pain, because her hour has come. But when her child is born, she no longer remembers the anguish because of the joy of having brought a human being into the world.
43推 16:22 So you have pain now; but I will see you again, and your hearts will rejoice, and no one will take your joy from you.
43推 16:23 On that day you will ask nothing of me. Very truly, I tell you, if you ask anything of the Father in my name, he will give it to you.
43推 16:24 Until now you have not asked for anything in my name. Ask and you will receive, so that your joy may be complete.
43推 16:25 "I have said these things to you in figures of speech. The hour is coming when I will no longer speak to you in figures, but will tell you plainly of the Father.
43推 16:26 On that day you will ask in my name. I do not say to you that I will ask the Father on your behalf;
43推 16:27 for the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me and have believed that I came from God.
43推 16:28 I came from the Father and have come into the world; again, I am leaving the world and am going to the Father."
43推 16:29 His disciples said, "Yes, now you are speaking plainly, not in any figure of speech!
43推 16:30 Now we know that you know all things, and do not need to have anyone question you; by this we believe that you came from God."
43推 16:31 Jesus answered them, "Do you now believe?
43推 16:32 The hour is coming, indeed it has come, when you will be scattered, each one to his home, and you will leave me alone. Yet I am not alone because the Father is with me.
43推 16:33 I have said this to you, so that in me you may have peace. In the world you face persecution. But take courage; I have conquered the world!"
43推 17:1 After Jesus had spoken these words, he looked up to heaven and said, "Father, the hour has come; glorify your Son so that the Son may glorify you,
43推 17:2 since you have given him authority over all people, to give eternal life to all whom you have given him.
43推 17:3 And this is eternal life, that they may know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ whom you have sent.
43推 17:4 I glorified you on earth by finishing the work that you gave me to do.
43推 17:5 So now, Father, glorify me in your own presence with the glory that I had in your presence before the world existed.
43推 17:6 "I have made your name known to those whom you gave me from the world. They were yours, and you gave them to me, and they have kept your word.
43推 17:7 Now they know that everything you have given me is from you;
43推 17:8 for the words that you gave to me I have given to them, and they have received them and know in truth that I came from you; and they have believed that you sent me.
43推 17:9 I am asking on their behalf; I am not asking on behalf of the world, but on behalf of those whom you gave me, because they are yours.
43推 17:10 All mine are yours, and yours are mine; and I have been glorified in them.
43推 17:11 And now I am no longer in the world, but they are in the world, and I am coming to you. Holy Father, protect them in your name that you have given me, so that they may be one, as we are one.
43推 17:12 While I was with them, I protected them in your name that you have given me. I guarded them, and not one of them was lost except the one destined to be lost, so that the scripture might be fulfilled.
43推 17:13 But now I am coming to you, and I speak these things in the world so that they may have my joy made complete in themselves.
43推 17:14 I have given them your word, and the world has hated them because they do not belong to the world, just as I do not belong to the world.
43推 17:15 I am not asking you to take them out of the world, but I ask you to protect them from the evil one.
43推 17:16 They do not belong to the world, just as I do not belong to the world.
43推 17:17 Sanctify them in the truth; your word is truth.
43推 17:18 As you have sent me into the world, so I have sent them into the world.
43推 17:19 And for their sakes I sanctify myself, so that they also may be sanctified in truth.
43推 17:20 "I ask not only on behalf of these, but also on behalf of those who will believe in me through their word,
43推 17:21 that they may all be one. As you, Father, are in me and I am in you, may they also be in us, so that the world may believe that you have sent me.
43推 17:22 The glory that you have given me I have given them, so that they may be one, as we are one,
43推 17:23 I in them and you in me, that they may become completely one, so that the world may know that you have sent me and have loved them even as you have loved me.
43推 17:24 Father, I desire that those also, whom you have given me, may be with me where I am, to see my glory, which you have given me because you loved me before the foundation of the world.
43推 17:25 "Righteous Father, the world does not know you, but I know you; and these know that you have sent me.
43推 17:26 I made your name known to them, and I will make it known, so that the love with which you have loved me may be in them, and I in them."
43推 18:1 After Jesus had spoken these words, he went out with his disciples across the Kidron valley to a place where there was a garden, which he and his disciples entered.
43推 18:2 Now Judas, who betrayed him, also knew the place, because Jesus often met there with his disciples.
43推 18:3 So Judas brought a detachment of soldiers together with police from the chief priests and the Pharisees, and they came there with lanterns and torches and weapons.
43推 18:4 Then Jesus, knowing all that was to happen to him, came forward and asked them, "Whom are you looking for?"
43推 18:5 They answered, "Jesus of Nazareth." Jesus replied, "I am he." Judas, who betrayed him, was standing with them.
43推 18:6 When Jesus said to them, "I am he," they stepped back and fell to the ground.
43推 18:7 Again he asked them, "Whom are you looking for?" And they said, "Jesus of Nazareth."
43推 18:8 Jesus answered, "I told you that I am he. So if you are looking for me, let these men go."
43推 18:9 This was to fulfill the word that he had spoken, "I did not lose a single one of those whom you gave me."
43推 18:10 Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, drew it, struck the high priest's slave, and cut off his right ear. The slave's name was Malchus.
43推 18:11 Jesus said to Peter, "Put your sword back into its sheath. Am I not to drink the cup that the Father has given me?"
43推 18:12 So the soldiers, their officer, and the Jewish police arrested Jesus and bound him.
43推 18:13 First they took him to Annas, who was the father-in-law of Caiaphas, the high priest that year.
43推 18:14 Caiaphas was the one who had advised the Jews that it was better to have one person die for the people.
43推 18:15 Simon Peter and another disciple followed Jesus. Since that disciple was known to the high priest, he went with Jesus into the courtyard of the high priest,
43推 18:16 but Peter was standing outside at the gate. So the other disciple, who was known to the high priest, went out, spoke to the woman who guarded the gate, and brought Peter in.
43推 18:17 The woman said to Peter, "You are not also one of this man's disciples, are you?" He said, "I am not."
43推 18:18 Now the slaves and the police had made a charcoal fire because it was cold, and they were standing around it and warming themselves. Peter also was standing with them and warming himself.
43推 18:19 Then the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching.
43推 18:20 Jesus answered, "I have spoken openly to the world; I have always taught in synagogues and in the temple, where all the Jews come together. I have said nothing in secret.
43推 18:21 Why do you ask me? Ask those who heard what I said to them; they know what I said."
43推 18:22 When he had said this, one of the police standing nearby struck Jesus on the face, saying, "Is that how you answer the high priest?"
43推 18:23 Jesus answered, "If I have spoken wrongly, testify to the wrong. But if I have spoken rightly, why do you strike me?"
43推 18:24 Then Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas the high priest.
43推 18:25 Now Simon Peter was standing and warming himself. They asked him, "You are not also one of his disciples, are you?" He denied it and said, "I am not."
43推 18:26 One of the slaves of the high priest, a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, asked, "Did I not see you in the garden with him?"
43推 18:27 Again Peter denied it, and at that moment the cock crowed.
43推 18:28 Then they took Jesus from Caiaphas to Pilate's headquarters. It was early in the morning. They themselves did not enter the headquarters, so as to avoid ritual defilement and to be able to eat the Passover.
43推 18:29 So Pilate went out to them and said, "What accusation do you bring against this man?"
43推 18:30 They answered, "If this man were not a criminal, we would not have handed him over to you."
43推 18:31 Pilate said to them, "Take him yourselves and judge him according to your law." The Jews replied, "We are not permitted to put anyone to death."
43推 18:32 (This was to fulfill what Jesus had said when he indicated the kind of death he was to die.)
43推 18:33 Then Pilate entered the headquarters again, summoned Jesus, and asked him, "Are you the King of the Jews?"
43推 18:34 Jesus answered, "Do you ask this on your own, or did others tell you about me?"
43推 18:35 Pilate replied, "I am not a Jew, am I? Your own nation and the chief priests have handed you over to me. What have you done?"
43推 18:36 Jesus answered, "My kingdom is not from this world. If my kingdom were from this world, my followers would be fighting to keep me from being handed over to the Jews. But as it is, my kingdom is not from here."
43推 18:37 Pilate asked him, "So you are a king?" Jesus answered, "You say that I am a king. For this I was born, and for this I came into the world, to testify to the truth. Everyone who belongs to the truth listens to my voice."
43推 18:38 Pilate asked him, "What is truth?" After he had said this, he went out to the Jews again and told them, "I find no case against him.
43推 18:39 But you have a custom that I release someone for you at the Passover. Do you want me to release for you the King of the Jews?"
43推 18:40 They shouted in reply, "Not this man, but Barabbas!" Now Barabbas was a bandit.
43推 19:1 Then Pilate took Jesus and had him flogged.
43推 19:2 And the soldiers wove a crown of thorns and put it on his head, and they dressed him in a purple robe.
43推 19:3 They kept coming up to him, saying, "Hail, King of the Jews!" and striking him on the face.
43推 19:4 Pilate went out again and said to them, "Look, I am bringing him out to you to let you know that I find no case against him."
43推 19:5 So Jesus came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. Pilate said to them, "Here is the man!"
43推 19:6 When the chief priests and the police saw him, they shouted, "Crucify him! Crucify him!" Pilate said to them, "Take him yourselves and crucify him; I find no case against him."
43推 19:7 The Jews answered him, "We have a law, and according to that law he ought to die because he has claimed to be the Son of God."
43推 19:8 Now when Pilate heard this, he was more afraid than ever.
43推 19:9 He entered his headquarters again and asked Jesus, "Where are you from?" But Jesus gave him no answer.
43推 19:10 Pilate therefore said to him, "Do you refuse to speak to me? Do you not know that I have power to release you, and power to crucify you?"
43推 19:11 Jesus answered him, "You would have no power over me unless it had been given you from above; therefore the one who handed me over to you is guilty of a greater sin."
43推 19:12 From then on Pilate tried to release him, but the Jews cried out, "If you release this man, you are no friend of the emperor. Everyone who claims to be a king sets himself against the emperor."
43推 19:13 When Pilate heard these words, he brought Jesus outside and sat on the judge's bench at a place called The Stone Pavement, or in Hebrew Gabbatha.
43推 19:14 Now it was the day of Preparation for the Passover; and it was about noon. He said to the Jews, "Here is your King!"
43推 19:15 They cried out, "Away with him! Away with him! Crucify him!" Pilate asked them, "Shall I crucify your King?" The chief priests answered, "We have no king but the emperor."
43推 19:16 Then he handed him over to them to be crucified. So they took Jesus;
43推 19:17 and carrying the cross by himself, he went out to what is called The Place of the Skull, which in Hebrew is called Golgotha.
43推 19:18 There they crucified him, and with him two others, one on either side, with Jesus between them.
43推 19:19 Pilate also had an inscription written and put on the cross. It read, "Jesus of Nazareth, the King of the Jews."
43推 19:20 Many of the Jews read this inscription, because the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city; and it was written in Hebrew, in Latin, and in Greek.
43推 19:21 Then the chief priests of the Jews said to Pilate, "Do not write, 'The King of the Jews,' but, 'This man said, I am King of the Jews.'"
43推 19:22 Pilate answered, "What I have written I have written."
43推 19:23 When the soldiers had crucified Jesus, they took his clothes and divided them into four parts, one for each soldier. They also took his tunic; now the tunic was seamless, woven in one piece from the top.
43推 19:24 So they said to one another, "Let us not tear it, but cast lots for it to see who will get it." This was to fulfill what the scripture says, "They divided my clothes among themselves, and for my clothing they cast lots."
43推 19:25 And that is what the soldiers did. Meanwhile, standing near the cross of Jesus were his mother, and his mother's sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene.
43推 19:26 When Jesus saw his mother and the disciple whom he loved standing beside her, he said to his mother, "Woman, here is your son."
43推 19:27 Then he said to the disciple, "Here is your mother." And from that hour the disciple took her into his own home.
43推 19:28 After this, when Jesus knew that all was now finished, he said (in order to fulfill the scripture), "I am thirsty."
43推 19:29 A jar full of sour wine was standing there. So they put a sponge full of the wine on a branch of hyssop and held it to his mouth.
43推 19:30 When Jesus had received the wine, he said, "It is finished." Then he bowed his head and gave up his spirit.
43推 19:31 Since it was the day of Preparation, the Jews did not want the bodies left on the cross during the sabbath, especially because that sabbath was a day of great solemnity. So they asked Pilate to have the legs of the crucified men broken and the bodies removed.
43推 19:32 Then the soldiers came and broke the legs of the first and of the other who had been crucified with him.
43推 19:33 But when they came to Jesus and saw that he was already dead, they did not break his legs.
43推 19:34 Instead, one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and at once blood and water came out.
43推 19:35 (He who saw this has testified so that you also may believe. His testimony is true, and he knows that he tells the truth.)
43推 19:36 These things occurred so that the scripture might be fulfilled, "None of his bones shall be broken."
43推 19:37 And again another passage of scripture says, "They will look on the one whom they have pierced."
43推 19:38 After these things, Joseph of Arimathea, who was a disciple of Jesus, though a secret one because of his fear of the Jews, asked Pilate to let him take away the body of Jesus. Pilate gave him permission; so he came and removed his body.
43推 19:39 Nicodemus, who had at first come to Jesus by night, also came, bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes, weighing about a hundred pounds.
43推 19:40 They took the body of Jesus and wrapped it with the spices in linen cloths, according to the burial custom of the Jews.
43推 19:41 Now there was a garden in the place where he was crucified, and in the garden there was a new tomb in which no one had ever been laid.
43推 19:42 And so, because it was the Jewish day of Preparation, and the tomb was nearby, they laid Jesus there.
43推 20:1 Early on the first day of the week, while it was still dark, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb and saw that the stone had been removed from the tomb.
43推 20:2 So she ran and went to Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one whom Jesus loved, and said to them, "They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him."
43推 20:3 Then Peter and the other disciple set out and went toward the tomb.
43推 20:4 The two were running together, but the other disciple outran Peter and reached the tomb first.
43推 20:5 He bent down to look in and saw the linen wrappings lying there, but he did not go in.
43推 20:6 Then Simon Peter came, following him, and went into the tomb. He saw the linen wrappings lying there,
43推 20:7 and the cloth that had been on Jesus' head, not lying with the linen wrappings but rolled up in a place by itself.
43推 20:8 Then the other disciple, who reached the tomb first, also went in, and he saw and believed;
43推 20:9 for as yet they did not understand the scripture, that he must rise from the dead.
43推 20:10 Then the disciples returned to their homes.
43推 20:11 But Mary stood weeping outside the tomb. As she wept, she bent over to look into the tomb;
43推 20:12 and she saw two angels in white, sitting where the body of Jesus had been lying, one at the head and the other at the feet.
43推 20:13 They said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping?" She said to them, "They have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have laid him."
43推 20:14 When she had said this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing there, but she did not know that it was Jesus.
43推 20:15 Jesus said to her, "Woman, why are you weeping? Whom are you looking for?" Supposing him to be the gardener, she said to him, "Sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away."
43推 20:16 Jesus said to her, "Mary!" She turned and said to him in Hebrew, "Rabbouni!" (which means Teacher).
43推 20:17 Jesus said to her, "Do not hold on to me, because I have not yet ascended to the Father. But go to my brothers and say to them, 'I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.'"
43推 20:18 Mary Magdalene went and announced to the disciples, "I have seen the Lord"; and she told them that he had said these things to her.
43推 20:19 When it was evening on that day, the first day of the week, and the doors of the house where the disciples had met were locked for fear of the Jews, Jesus came and stood among them and said, "Peace be with you."
43推 20:20 After he said this, he showed them his hands and his side. Then the disciples rejoiced when they saw the Lord.
43推 20:21 Jesus said to them again, "Peace be with you. As the Father has sent me, so I send you."
43推 20:22 When he had said this, he breathed on them and said to them, "Receive the Holy Spirit.
43推 20:23 If you forgive the sins of any, they are forgiven them; if you retain the sins of any, they are retained."
43推 20:24 But Thomas (who was called the Twin), one of the twelve, was not with them when Jesus came.
43推 20:25 So the other disciples told him, "We have seen the Lord." But he said to them, "Unless I see the mark of the nails in his hands, and put my finger in the mark of the nails and my hand in his side, I will not believe."
43推 20:26 A week later his disciples were again in the house, and Thomas was with them. Although the doors were shut, Jesus came and stood among them and said, "Peace be with you."
43推 20:27 Then he said to Thomas, "Put your finger here and see my hands. Reach out your hand and put it in my side. Do not doubt but believe."
43推 20:28 Thomas answered him, "My Lord and my God!"
43推 20:29 Jesus said to him, "Have you believed because you have seen me? Blessed are those who have not seen and yet have come to believe."
43推 20:30 Now Jesus did many other signs in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book.
43推 20:31 But these are written so that you may come to believe that Jesus is the Messiah, the Son of God, and that through believing you may have life in his name.
43推 21:1 After these things Jesus showed himself again to the disciples by the Sea of Tiberias; and he showed himself in this way.
43推 21:2 Gathered there together were Simon Peter, Thomas called the Twin, Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee, and two others of his disciples.
43推 21:3 Simon Peter said to them, "I am going fishing." They said to him, "We will go with you." They went out and got into the boat, but that night they caught nothing.
43推 21:4 Just after daybreak, Jesus stood on the beach; but the disciples did not know that it was Jesus.
43推 21:5 Jesus said to them, "Children, you have no fish, have you?" They answered him, "No."
43推 21:6 He said to them, "Cast the net to the right side of the boat, and you will find some." So they cast it, and now they were not able to haul it in because there were so many fish.
43推 21:7 That disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, "It is the Lord!" When Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he put on some clothes, for he was naked, and jumped into the sea.
43推 21:8 But the other disciples came in the boat, dragging the net full of fish, for they were not far from the land, only about a hundred yards off.
43推 21:9 When they had gone ashore, they saw a charcoal fire there, with fish on it, and bread.
43推 21:10 Jesus said to them, "Bring some of the fish that you have just caught."
43推 21:11 So Simon Peter went aboard and hauled the net ashore, full of large fish, a hundred fifty-three of them; and though there were so many, the net was not torn.
43推 21:12 Jesus said to them, "Come and have breakfast." Now none of the disciples dared to ask him, "Who are you?" because they knew it was the Lord.
43推 21:13 Jesus came and took the bread and gave it to them, and did the same with the fish.
43推 21:14 This was now the third time that Jesus appeared to the disciples after he was raised from the dead.
43推 21:15 When they had finished breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, "Simon son of John, do you love me more than these?" He said to him, "Yes, Lord; you know that I love you." Jesus said to him, "Feed my lambs."
43推 21:16 A second time he said to him, "Simon son of John, do you love me?" He said to him, "Yes, Lord; you know that I love you." Jesus said to him, "Tend my sheep."
43推 21:17 He said to him the third time, "Simon son of John, do you love me?" Peter felt hurt because he said to him the third time, "Do you love me?" And he said to him, "Lord, you know everything; you know that I love you." Jesus said to him, "Feed my sheep.
43推 21:18 Very truly, I tell you, when you were younger, you used to fasten your own belt and to go wherever you wished. But when you grow old, you will stretch out your hands, and someone else will fasten a belt around you and take you where you do not wish to go."
43推 21:19 (He said this to indicate the kind of death by which he would glorify God.) After this he said to him, "Follow me."
43推 21:20 Peter turned and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following them; he was the one who had reclined next to Jesus at the supper and had said, "Lord, who is it that is going to betray you?"
43推 21:21 When Peter saw him, he said to Jesus, "Lord, what about him?"
43推 21:22 Jesus said to him, "If it is my will that he remain until I come, what is that to you? Follow me!"
43推 21:23 So the rumor spread in the community that this disciple would not die. Yet Jesus did not say to him that he would not die, but, "If it is my will that he remain until I come, what is that to you?"
43推 21:24 This is the disciple who is testifying to these things and has written them, and we know that his testimony is true.
43推 21:25 But there are also many other things that Jesus did; if every one of them were written down, I suppose that the world itself could not contain the books that would be written.
